title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Combine all ingredients. Cover 5 (10-inch) flour tortillas; roll up. Refrigerate until set. Slice in 1/2-inch pieces. Dip in your favorite salsa. Great for parties/showers.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Crumble biscuits until fine crumbs.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put into a pan or dish and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Spread cream cheese over slice of ham.
Place scallions at one end.
Roll up.
Insert toothpicks and cut between toothpicks in 1-inch sections.

title: pasta cohen
directions: Saute shallots and olive oil until transparent. Add mushrooms, sherry, cream, tomato sauce and basil; stir. Simmer for 1/2 hour. Pour over pasta.

title: saucy meat loaf
directions: Mix and shape into loaf and put in shallow pan.
Spread topping over loaf and bake about an hour at 350°.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until fluffy. Add flour and sugar. Mix well. Chill 1 hour. Shape into balls. Press into greased muffin tins.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots and set aside.
Melt butter and brown sugar. Add the cinnamon to melted mixture.
Combine with the carrots and serve.

title: ranch gate casserole
directions: Stir soups until smooth.
Add milk, onions and peppers.
Place 1 cup in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cut 10 long strips from 3 tortillas.
Set aside.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Split zucchini in halves lengthwise and scoop out seeds and membrane.
Set aside.
Saute green pepper and onion in butter until onion is transparent.
Remove and set aside.
Brown ground beef, separating with a fork.
Add green pepper, onion and remaining ingredients.
Place zucchini halves in a well-greased baking pan.
Fill each half with corn stuffing.
Pour 1/2 cup water in the bottom of the pan; cover with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven until zucchini is tender.
Remove foil and bake an additional 1/2 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate pie surprise
directions: Bake pie crust at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle bottom of hot pie crust with chocolate chips. When they melt, spread around to coat evenly.
Cool.
Meanwhile, whip cream cheese until fluffy.
Add vanilla at this time, if desired.
Spread over chocolate layer in pie crust.
Mix together the pudding and cold milk.
Whip until smooth and thick; set aside 5 minutes.
Blend in the whipped cream, mixing well.
Spread over cream cheese layer in pie crust.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour or longer.
Before serving, garnish with candy orange slices.

title: baked apples
directions: Mix sugar and apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and cloves and dot with butter.
Put in crock-pot.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cook on low 7 to 9 hours, high 2 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into freezer.
Add milk to fill and freeze.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into greased casserole dish.

title: mrs. gardner's secret chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat cup of butter until soft.
Add to butter, brown sugar and regular sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift the following dry ingredients together and add to the mixture, baking powder, baking soda, flour and salt.
Add a large package of chocolate chips and toasted pecans (toast pecans at 400° for about 10 minutes).
Bake cookies at 350° until pale brown.
Tear up this recipe; it is very secret, and you should not be caught with it!

title: chicken n macaroni bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare a 2-quart casserole dish with cooking spray; set aside.
In a skillet, heat oil over medium heat. Add chicken and onions.
Cook until chicken is no longer pink and onions are tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and basil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner according to package directions (I use skim milk and fat-free spread).
Spread chicken mixture onto bottom of prepared pan.
Top with macaroni dinner.

title: vegetable taco dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix it with hot salsa.
Put into serving dish and refrigerate to set.
Top with medium salsa and spread it over cream cheese mixture.
Mix all vegetables and put on top of medium salsa.
Sprinkle cheese on top of vegetables. Use as dip with taco chips.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart serving bowl, layer lettuce, pepper, corn, tomatoes and celery.
Spread mayonnaise over the celery layer, sealing to edges of bowl; cover.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon before serving.

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add all but milk and eggs.
Beat milk and eggs together.

title: baked can beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Add remaining ingredients; put in greased 2-quart dish and top with crushed bacon.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a flat baking dish (6-1/2x10-1/2x1-3/4 inches) and place in a slow oven (300°F.) and bake for 1 1/2 hours or until rice is perfectly tender and pudding is thick and creamy.
NOT DRY.

title: pineapple-upside down cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy; add egg and vanilla.

title: spanish pork chops with rice
directions: Brown chops in skillet with oil.
Add onion and celery and brown.
After removing chops, put onion and celery in baking dish. Place chops on top.
Put a mound of rice on each chop.
Pour tomato juice around chops.
Sprinkle parsley on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time. Add bananas, lemon juice and milk.
Put dry ingredients together and stir into batter.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool on cake rack.

title: peanut butter fudge 1
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in saucepan. Boil to soft boil stage (approximately 8 minutes). Take off heat, add peanut butter, marshmallow cream. Mix well and pour into buttered 9x13 pan. Cool. Cut in squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli just until it separates; drain well.
Melt oleo and cheese over low heat; stir until well blended.
Add broccoli; mix thoroughly.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover top of casserole with cracker crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Blend in milk and vanilla.
Chill mixture for 2 hours or until firm. Drain cherries; dry on absorbent paper towel.
Place bowl of sugar mixture in a bowl of ice to keep chilled.
Shape a small amount of sugar around each cherry.
Place on waxed paper-lined cookie sheet; chill 2 hours or until firm.
Melt chocolate and shortening in double boiler.
Dip each cherry by stem.
Place on wax paper-lined cookie sheet.
Chill.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: pat's old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Crumble biscuits.
Pour in milk and let stand until dissolved. Add eggs, butter, sugar and vanilla.
Bake in small baking dish at 375° until brown.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat all but blueberries.
Gently fold in berries.
Cook about 20 minutes at 350° in greased muffin pans.

title: layered southwestern dip
directions: In a small bowl mix chili seasoning with 1 1/2 cups of the sour cream; set aside.
In another small bowl mix 1/2 cup sour cream into the guacamole.
Layer the refried beans, guacamole, and sour cream mixture (one layer each) in a large deep dish in the order listed.
Sprinkle with the shredded cheese, chopped green onions, olives, and diced tomatoes.
Chill for 1 hour to blend flavors.
Serve with your favorite chips.
Makes 8-10 servings.

title: fritter batter(onion rings)
directions: Beat eggs, then stir in milk.
Beat in next 3 ingredients. Add oil.
Cut onions 1/4-inch thick; dip in batter to coat.
Deep fry until brown.
Drain on paper towel and serve immediately.

title: turkey dressing(mama williams' style)
directions: Cook celery and onion until tender (save broth).
Mix sage, poultry seasoning and dressing mix.

Stir well the eggs and butter with dry ingredients, adding only as much broth as needed to make a moist stuffing for cavities of turkey and/ or make small patties and place on baking sheet and lightly brown in oven.
Good with turkey gravy poured over patties.

title: busy day cake
directions: Beat all together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: he-man hash
directions: Brown meat and drain grease.
Add the rest of the ingredients and stir over moderate heat until bubbly.
Lower heat and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve over rice or egg noodles.
Sprinkle with Chinese noodles.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine ingredients and place in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: venetian pie (meat pie)
directions: Simmer on low while preparing crust.

title: sonya's hot beef dip
directions: Melt cream cheese & butter.
Add remaining ingredients to pan & heat.
Serve warm with corn chips.

title: peanut chews
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter and egg.
Press in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 12 minutes to set.
Pour the miniature marshmallows over warm crust and return to oven just until they begin to puff.
In a saucepan, melt the Reese's peanut butter chips with corn syrup.
Stir in vanilla and pour over peanuts and Rice Krispies.
Mix well and spoon over crust/marshmallows.
Allow to set.
Cut into squares and enjoy!

title: chicken loaf
directions: Mix
and
shape into loaf.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: italian coconut cream cake
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs, oleo and oil.
Add flour, soda, buttermilk, coconut, vanilla and pecans.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Bake in three 8 or 9-inch pans at 350°.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix together in large bowl. When serving, put 1/4 cup powder in tea cup. Fill with hot water. Add marshmallows, if desired.

title: california egg crackle
directions: Fry diced bacon; drain excess grease.
Add milk and well beaten eggs.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir constantly.
Just before eggs become completely dry, add crushed cheese crackers. Serves 12.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer each item in a casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: a.1. stuffed peppers
directions: Brown ground beef and onions until done; drain.
Stir in corn, sauce, rice, steak sauce and pepper.
Spoon mixture into peppers. Put into baking dish.
Bake at 350° until peppers are done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ground beef and bean casserole(corn bread and hamburger pie)
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and fry together until meat and onions turn white.
Add chili powder if desired.
Pour over pintos.
Cover with corn meal mix (real thin).
Bake in oven at 350° until bread browns.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine water and sugar; stir until sugar dissolves. Add milk and eggs. Stir in coconut and next 5 ingredients. Add rice and let stand for 30 minutes. Pour into a 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Prepare and cook corn.
Cook and stir onion and green pepper until tender.
Remove from heat; stir in flour, salt, paprika, dry mustard and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly. Remove from heat; stir in milk gradually. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute; stir in corn and egg.
Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole.
Mix crumbs and 1 tablespoon of butter; sprinkle over corn.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° until bubbly, approximately 30 to 35 minutes.

title: 10 can chicken casserole
directions: Use about 15 x 2 1/2-inch (3-quart) casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together.
Top with 2 cans of French fried onions rings.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serves 12 to 15 people.
Can be frozen and used later.

title: cheese dip(chili con queso)
directions: Drain the juice from the Ro-Tel into a large pot.
Add the cheese in chunks and melt on medium heat.
Fry the sausage in a skillet until crumbly.
Cut up the tomatoes into small pieces. Add the tomatoes to the sausage and finish cooking.
Then add the cheese mix and heat until piping hot.
Serve with plain taco chips.

title: heavenly hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler; add chocolate and blend. Add sugar, milk and salt and cook on low heat, stirring frequently for 20 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes one quart.

title: fluffy meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into loaf in shallow baking pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening over low heat.
Let cool.
Add sugar, egg, molasses: beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, cloves, ginger, cinnamon and salt; add to first mixture.
Mix well: chill.
Form in 1 inch balls, roll in granulated sugar and place on greased cookie sheet two inches apart.
Bake in moderately hot oven, 375 degrees, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat cheeses on medium speed until fluffy.
Mix in onion and Worcestershire sauce; add lemon juice, pimento and butter.
Stir in pecans.
Cover and chill 3 to 4 hours.
Mold into a large ball. Cover and chill until firm, about 2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit; save juice.
Add pudding mix to juice; add lemon juice.
Mix with drained fruit and chill overnight.
Just before serving, add bananas.

title: camper's baked fish
directions: After fish has been cleaned, rub 1/2 inch crust of mud all over each fish.
Carefully lay fish into hot coals.
Spread additional
hot coals over top of fish.
Do not disturb while cooking, it may crack the mud.
Most fish will cook in 1/2 hour. Remove from fire and crack mud pack carefully.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly in a 2-quart bowl.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup and melted butter.
Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked shell. Bake near center of oven for 35 to 40 minutes, or until filling is slightly firm in a 375° oven.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix together pineapple and pie filling and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix, nuts and coconut over fruit. Melt oleo and pour over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature. Add all ingredients together. Refrigerate overnight.

title: alice's hunter's special
directions: Tenderize slices of deer tenderloin.
Melt shortening in frying pan.
Dip pieces of tenderloin in seasoned flour.
Brown quickly on each side.
Take up and set aside.
Drain off all shortening, except 3 tablespoons.
Saute onions in shortening. Brown and add the Ro-Tel tomatoes, mashed.
Add 1 cup water.
Cook until thick.
Add dash of hot sauce and enough catsup to color. Can place meat back in gravy or leave out.
Serve over wild rice or biscuits.

title: low-fat seafood dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and crab.
Thinly spread shrimp cocktail sauce over top.
Good with Snack Wells fat-free wheat crackers.

title: chocolate nut surprises
directions: Mix oleo and vanilla wafers; spread in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add coconut, chips and nuts; add the milk over the top.
Place cherries over mixture.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: blueberry crumb cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Then cream butter and sugar in separate bowl.
Add egg and beat until smooth. Then add the dry ingredients and milk.
Now fold in blueberries. Pour mixture into a greased 10 3/4 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Sprinkle on prepared topping.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and Crisco together. Add eggs, one at a time, beating good after each one.
Add flour and half and half alternately, ending with flour.
Add baking powder, salt and vanilla. Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan (makes one big cake).
Put in cold oven at 325° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Watch after 1 hour.
My oven cooks fast and it only takes 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: frosted salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water, stirring until well dissolved. Add 7-Up and chill until partly congealed.
Add 1 1/2 cups drained pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Put into refrigerator and chill.

title: vinegar sweet pickles(this recipe was made up by olive bowman.)
directions: Place fresh gathered cucumbers into jars cold.
It is better to quarter them and use enough small cucumbers to make a wedge in center of jars so they won't float.
Put warm solution over cucumbers and seal tightly with jars that have been placed in cold pack canner.
Let water boil over tops of jars for 10 minutes in order for them to seal.
Remove from canner and screw tightly. If you overprocess them, they will shrink and be no good.
Make several solutions for a great deal of cucumbers.
One solution will usually do for 3 quarts.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme in a bowl.
Cook sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Pour over peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into buttered 9-inch Pyrex.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine and bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in unbaked pie shells.
Bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
This makes 2 pies.

title: quick hash
directions: Brown meat, onion, bell pepper and celery.
Add chopped potatoes and carrots to mixture.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce (corn and salsa if desired), rosemary and chili powder.
Season to taste with Mrs. Dash, salt and pepper.
Cook for about 45 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put into a casserole.
Cover with topping.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, milk and egg well.
Add potatoes to mixture and spread in pan.

title: strawberry torte
directions: Beat egg white until stiff peaks form. Add sugar, crackers, nuts and vanilla and blend well. Grease a 9 X 13 pan. Spread mixture in pan and bake at 350 degree oven for 20-25 minutes. Let cool, Clean and slice strawberries fold into cool whip and spread over cooled crust. Garnish with a few slices of strawberry.

title: peanut butter halloween candy
directions: Combine ingredients and spread in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Melt 12 ounces chocolate.
Spread on top.
Chill and cut into 40 pieces.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Prepare pineapple cake according to package directions.
Leave cake in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and boil for 5 minutes. Pour over hot cake.
This cake is better after it sits.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add liquid; mix well.
Will be stiff; do not stir again.
Fill tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Will keep in fridge for 6 weeks.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Combine soy sauce, vinegar and garlic.

title: monte cristo sandwiches
directions: In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, nutmeg and pepper. Spread on one side of each bread slice. Layer ham, chicken or turkey on 6 bread slices. Top with remaining bread, mayonnaise side down. Cut sandwiches diagonally into quarters. In small bowl, beat together eggs and milk. Dip sandwich quarters into egg mixture. Cook on preheated griddle or skillet, turning once, 4 to 5 minutes or until browned and heated through. Serve with raspberry preserves. Makes 24 mini sandwiches.

title: jon's world famous french toast
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread.
Dip bread into mixture and brown in a skillet.
Makes 12 slices.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Prepare sugar cookie dough on pizza pan.
(Follow instructions on label.)
Place in refrigerator to cool.
Blend cream cheese and sugar until smooth (add more sugar if necessary).
Spread onto cold cookie.
Cut strawberries, kiwi and pineapple in halves. Alternate in rows, beginning at the outside of the cookie.
Store in the refrigerator until time to serve.

title: souffle potatoes
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes according to package directions.
Add egg, onions and salt, stirring until blended.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, then bake, uncovered, at 350° for 5 minutes or until cheese melts. Yields 8 servings.

title: easy banana cream pie
directions: Place bananas in bottom of crust.
Mix milk, lemon juice, and almond extract and pour over bananas.
Top with cool whip.
Chill and serve.

title: haeran's korean beef
directions: Cut beef tenderloin or lean beef into thin strips and sprinkle with sugar; set aside for 30 minutes.
Combine soy, pepper, garlic, onion, etc. with 1 tablespoon sugar; mix into beef and let marinate for 30 minutes more.
Place foil on a hot grill; puncture foil all over with a fork.
Place meat on foil and cook, stirring as you would stir-fry, until done.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cranberry raspberry relish
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
(May be refrigerated, covered, for up to 1 month.)
Makes 6 cups.
Serves 12.

title: go bananas ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.
Freeze in a 1 gallon ice cream freezer.

title: broccoli-ham-rice
directions: Cook 1 cup rice with the chicken broth.
Set aside.
"This will make 2 cups cooked rice."
In large skillet or Dutch oven, melt butter.
Add onion, celery, broccoli, mushrooms and chestnuts.
Cook until tender.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in large casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar; add rest of ingredients and stir. Let stand for 2 days.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: classic sour cream cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs and margarine; press firmly in a 9-inch pie pan.
Blend cheese in a large mixing bowl until fluffy.
Add sweet cream and blend until smooth.
Beat in eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into pie pan and bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool, chill and garnish as desired.

title: mayo cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: In large saucepan, beat together milk, sugar, eggs, flour and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture reaches 160° or until just coats a metal spoon.
Cool quickly by placing pan in a bowl of ice or cold water; continue to stir.
Add half and half and heavy cream.
Combine well.
Add desired flavorings.
Freeze according to ice cream maker's instructions.

title: garden skillet supper
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Saute onion and garlic until tender.
Flour squash and zucchini.
Add to onion mixture.
Add green pepper.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Cook 15 minutes longer.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar with electric mixer. Add molasses and egg. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Dough will be stiff. Cover and chill 1 hour. Roll out dough on lightly floured cutting board to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut dough with cookie cutter.
Place on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 22 to 24 (5-inch) cookies.

title: fettuccine vegetable toss
directions: Cook fettuccine per directions.
In deep 12-inch skillet, heat butter and oil.
Add broccoli and onion; cook 3 minutes, stirring often.
Add pea pods, mushrooms, peppers, garlic, salt and pepper. Cook and stir until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add cream and Parmesan cheese.
Cook for 3 minutes until blended and simmering. Drain fettuccine and add to skillet.
Stir until well mixed. Serve immediately.

title: grapenut bread
directions: Mix together grapenuts, sugar and buttermilk and let stand overnight. Add remaining ingredients and bake in loaf pan at 325 for 1 hour.

title: mustardy fried chicken bread
directions: Wipe chicken breasts with damp paper toweling.
Sprinkle with the salt and
pepper.
Beat
together egg and mustard.
In separate bowl, combine
Parmesan
cheese and bread crumbs.
Dip each
chicken
breast in
egg
mixture.
Then
roll
in
cheese mixture.
Lay chicken on
waxed
paper
and let set 10 minutes. Saute chicken on both sides
in heated oil for 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Sprinkle with green pepper slices.

title: pasta casserole
directions: Cook onion and garlic in olive oil until soft.
Add tomatoes, crushed red peppers, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Cook pasta and drain.
Mix Mozzarella cheese, pasta and spinach.
Add 2/3 cup Parmesan cheese; toss well.
Put into casserole dish, sprinkle with the rest of the Parmesan cheese.
Put under broiler until the cheese is golden brown.

title: english toffee balls
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, cream powdered sugar, butter and pudding mix.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir flour, milk and vanilla into creamed mixture; mix well.
Cut Hershey Nuggets in halves and shape dough around each half forming a ball.
Top each ball with a pecan half.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 13 to 18 minutes or until edges are light golden brown.
Cool.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: tin can bread(size 1 tin can)
directions: Bring raisins, butter and water to a boil; let cool.
Mix all together and put in 3 greased cans (size 2).
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Use toothpick to test and see if done.

title: donuts
directions: Soak yeast for 10 minutes in lukewarm water.
Mix shortening, sugar, salt and egg.
Add to yeast, then add flour and milk.
Let rise until doubled.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut doughnuts out and let rise again.
Fry in deep oil until golden brown.
Glaze with powdered sugar and milk mixture.

title: mason-dixon dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Heat chili in a saucepan for 5 minutes.
Press softened cream cheese into the bottom of a 1-1/2 qt. baking dish.
Pour chili over cream cheese, sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with green onions.	Serve with tortilla chips.

title: light and dark devil's food cake
directions: Mix well and cook on top of stove until thick, stirring constantly.

title: dill pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers into spears.
Bring liquids and salt to boil. Pack jars with cucumbers.
Add dill blossoms, garlic cloves and 1/2 teaspoon dill weed to each jar.
Pour liquid into jars.
Seal and let set.

title: good dip
directions: Mix all together.
Let stand 24 hours.
Keeps real good!

title: camper's tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add tomatoes.
Mix cornmeal and water and add to tomato mix by spoonfuls, stirring constantly.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chili powder, corn, olives, salt and pepper.
Heat through.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Pack mixture into greased bread pan and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: baked apricots
directions: Cut apricots in half and remove stone.	Place skin side up in individual ovenproof dishes or one larger one.
Put the water in a small saucepan.
Add crushed cardamon seeds, sugar and lemon zest, bring to a boil and simmer for 2 minutes.

title: starfruit punch
directions: In a large container, combine cranberry juice, pineapple juice, pink lemonade concentrate and water. In a round pan, small enough to fit into punch bowl, fill 1-inch warm water, add 5-7 drops blue food coloring and freeze. Slice 13 star shaped pieces from fruit and lay them in a circle formation along rim of round pan and cover with water. Freeze. Just before your party starts, fill bowl with punch ingredients and lemon lime soda. Add ice cake garnish.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°; preheat 2 tablespoons grease in pan.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine chicken broth and vegetables in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in chicken soup, chicken and pepper.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, milk and butter; pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Serves 8.
Good!

title: white trash
directions: Melt chocolate in 1 3/4 qt. casserole.
Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Pour melted chocolate over ingredients in bowl, Stir until well coated.
Pour onto waxed pepper to cool.
Break apart and store in tight container.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into graham cracker crusts. Chill several hours before serving.

title: milkless, eggless, butterless cake
directions: Mix first seven ingredients in pan.
Boil 5 minutes.
Cool in pan, then add flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 375° for about 35 to 45 minutes until done.

title: mushroom cheese
directions: Cook onion in butter until softened.
Add the mushrooms and cook until almost all the liquid is evaporated.
Add the Port and cook over high heat until all the liquid is evaporated.
Season with salt and pepper and let cook to room temperature.
In processor, grind Cheddar; add cream cheese and sour cream and blend until smooth.
Add mushrooms and process until fine.
Makes 45 mushrooms caps.

title: diabetic peanut butter cookies(calories: 198 for 3 cookies)
directions: Blend graham crackers with peanut butter.
Add liquid sweetening agent and baking powder.
Add egg yolk and mix thoroughly.
Mix in the milk thoroughly.
Form balls.
Place on a cookie sheet; press flat with a fork.
Bake in a moderate oven for about 10 minutes.

title: lo-cal soup
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cook until semi-soft, about 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, lemon and sugar.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Add green beans.
Cook for 10 minutes.
This soup keeps well for a week or can be put in containers and frozen.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain.
Add first five ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cut biscuits in half.
Place biscuits on top of casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over biscuits. Cook in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: shoepeg salad
directions: Mix and leave overnight.

title: date pinwheels
directions: Cook dates, water and walnuts, stirring constantly until thick.
Combine oleo and sugars and cream.
Add egg and beat well. Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients into cream mixture and mix until smooth.
Chill.
Divide and roll to about 1/4-inch.
Spread date mixture evenly over dough and roll like jelly roll.
Wrap in foil and put in freezer until needed, then slice and bake.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding; set aside.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Add pudding.
Crush Oreos and place in the bottom of a flowerpot.
Pour pudding mixture in flowerpot.
Add rest of crushed Oreos on top of pudding.
Add a small plastic flower or green plant in the center.

title: hasty hash(microwave)
directions: Place butter in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook on high 1 minute.
Stir in onion.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook on High 5 minutes, stirring once.
Combine water and gravy mix in a 2-cup glass measure.
Cook on High 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir at 1 minute intervals.
Combine beef and potatoes in a large mixing bowl.
Add onion, gravy, salt and pepper; blend well.
Spread mixture in a 12 x 8-inch glass dish.
Sprinkle with paprika; cover with wax paper and cook on High 14 to 16 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn after 7 to 8 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 2 to 3 minutes before serving.

title: loaf bread pie crust
directions: Best on cobblers (apple or peach).
Cut bread slices into strips.
Beat together egg, sugar, and melted butter or margarine. Prepare fruit and sweeten to taste.
Put into casserole dish.
Cut off crust and cut bread into 4 strips; lay over fruit.
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Smooth over all and bake until brown, about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: tater topped casserole
directions: Brown onion, celery and ground beef.
Add salt and pepper. Spread mixture in 2-quart greased baking dish.
Add peas or corn (if desired).
Pour soup over top.
Top with Tater Tots.

title: hot brown
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour, cooking 2 or 3 minutes without letting it brown.
Add the cream or milk slowly, cooking until thickened and smooth.
Stir in Cheddar cheese, nutmeg, cayenne, salt and pepper.
Heat over low fire until cheese is melted.

title: shrimp-gelatin salad
directions: Heat the soup and dissolve the gelatin in it.
Add water, mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into mold of choice.
Refrigerate.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine all of the ingredients, form size of steaks you like. Flour them and brown in hot fat.
You may: (1) put in casserole, add tomato soup or cream of mushroom soup and bake at 350° for 45 minutes; or, (2) simmer in electric skillet for 15 to 20 minutes, covered.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In plastic bag, combine potato flakes and poultry seasoning.
In shallow bowl, combine egg and lemon juice.

title: eggnog quick bread
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar, eggnog, butter, rum and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg together and add to egg mixture, stirring just until blended.

title: butterscotch lush
directions: Crumble margarine, flour and chopped nuts together and press in pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: tangy frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in 1 quart ice cream carton or stainless steel bowl and freeze.
Remove from carton or bowl. Slice and serve.

title: *pispilita with leeks(cornmeal leeks casserole)
directions: To Clean Leeks:
Remove dried outside leaves.
Cut off bottom "whiskers" and a little of the top tough leaves.
Cut leeks lengthwise and then cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Wash thoroughly to remove all sand. Drain well.

title: mock champagne
directions: In a large pitcher combine club soda, ginger ale and grape juice.
Mix gently.
Pour into chilled champagne flutes and serve immediately.
Makes 11 (1 cup) servings.

title: honey baked ham and noodle casserole
directions: Combine ingredients; salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 375° until it bubbles.

title: no-cook fudge
directions: Bring water to a boil with margarine until melted.
Stir in other ingredients; beat and pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan. Chill and cut.

title: t. j. miracle soup
directions: Cut vegetables in medium pieces and boil covered with water. Add soup mix or cubes and boil for 10 minutes.
Turn on low heat and simmer until vegetables are soft.

title: taco soup
directions: Use 14 to 15-ounce cans and do not drain them.
Stir well and simmer.
Serve with Doritos chips and sour cream.

title: cranberry frozen salad
directions: Add the sugar to
the
chopped cranberries and allow to stand for 2 hours.
Add
the pineapple, nuts, marshmallows and Dream Whip.
Mix thoroughly and freeze.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together in a bowl.
Cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 20 to 30 cookies.

title: beef a la milanesa
directions: Spice beef with salt, garlic and pepper.
In a soup plate, beat 2 eggs with a pinch of salt, 1 plate with flour and 1 plate with bread crumbs.

Pass each slice on flour, eggs and bread crumbs. Deep fry the slices in enough oil to cover them in medium fire. When they are golden brown and cooked inside, arrange them neatly in a glass tray with paper towel on the bottom to absorb oil.
Bon appetit!

title: goulash
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed; drain and add last four ingredients.
Mix well.
Great taste.

title: praise singers escalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Use electric skillet.
Preheat skillet to 350°.
Melt butter. Add ham cubes and brown on all sides.
Reduce temperature to 250°. Add onion, green pepper and potatoes.
Mix well.
Combine soup, milk and seasoning.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs. Cover, with vent closed, and cook 50 to 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Serves 6.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mix mustard and garlic.
Add egg, vinegar, salt and pepper; mix well.
Slowly add olive oil and again mix well.
Pour mixture over romaine lettuce and toss.
Add Parmesan cheese and croutons and toss again.
Serve.

title: turtle cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake according to directions.
Divide in half.
Pour 1/2 mix into pan.
Mix together 1/2 can milk and 1 stick melted margarine. Pour over cake and bake for 30 minutes.
Melt caramels with 1/2 can of milk and 1 stick margarine.
Beat well.
Pour over baked cake layer.
Spread evenly and sprinkle with nuts.
Pour remaining 1/2 cake batter in pan and bake for 30 minutes or until done.
Top with chocolate icing and nuts.

title: broccoli cheese bake
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Add cheese and 1/2 stick butter. Crumble crackers and mix with 1/2 stick butter.
Put cracker mixture on top of broccoli and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: south of the border mexican lasagna
directions: Line bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch baking pan with 6 tortillas. Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Add cumin, chili powder, garlic powder, salt, black pepper, red pepper and tomatoes; mix well.
Cook until heated through.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Top with remaining tortillas. Spread with mixture of cottage cheese, 1 cup Cheddar cheese and egg.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle diagonal rows of 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, green onions and olives over top.
Yields 8 servings.

title: dilly beans
directions: Pack jars with 1/4 tsp. pepper, 1 garlic clove, 1/2 tsp. or 1 head of dill, and green beans.
Heat water, vinegar, and salt to boiling.
Pour over beans.
Seal jars and process in boiling water for 10 minutes (pints or quarts).
Wait 3 weeks to eat.

title: z bread
directions: Mix all at once until well mixed (do not beat).
Pour into pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Use a 12-inch loaf pan or a tube cake pan.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Put sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt in a large mixing bowl. Put oleo, oil, cocoa and water in a medium saucepan and mix together.
Bring to a full boil.
Pour into the mixing bowl with the sugar mixture and beat for 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and beat again for 3 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in a greased cookie sheet pan.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cut the French bread into 1 1/2-inch cubes for 12 cups of cubes.
Drain the fruit cocktail and remove the cherries and drain the peach halves and cut into large chunks.

title: appetizer roll-ups
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with chopped vegetables.
Spread on tortilla shell, then roll tightly.
Refrigerate until ready to serve, then slice crosswise.

title: cheese grits
directions: Slowly stir grits into boiling water.
Remove from heat when thickened.
Add oleo, eggs (well beaten), cubed cheese and seasoning salt.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
May be made a day ahead and refrigerated.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: carioco candy
directions: Melt butterscotch and chocolate over medium heat.
When smooth, add noodles and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper to cool.
Refrigerate in airtight container.

title: vanilla, butter and nut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Fold in vanilla, butter and nut flavorings by hand.
Bake in a greased tube pan for 1 hour and 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: quick whole wheat bread
directions: Sift flours, baking powder, baking soda and salt into a bowl. Add the remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Spoon into a buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake about 50 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate chews
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1/3 cup milk.
Pat 1/2 of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: rocky road
directions: Pour chocolate over peanuts and marshmallows until covered. Spoon into small mounds on wax paper or pour into a sheet pan and cut into squares.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Divide baked cake in half.
Crumble 1 half of cake in large bowl (very large bowl).
Spread 1 mixture of instant pudding, spread 1 half of crushed pineapple, spread 1 can of cherry pie filling, sprinkle 1 package of chopped pecans.
Spread 1 container of Cool Whip.
Crumble the other half of cake on top and add remaining ingredients as above.
Make the night before (best if made a couple of nights before) and keep refrigerated.

title: carrie's chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter. Add other ingredients and mix well. Pour in unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Return to pot; add tomatoes, tomato paste, beans, salt, pepper, chili powder and bay leaf.
Simmer to boil; simmer 45 minutes.

title: cranberry-orange relish(no cooking)
directions: Put berries and orange through food processor until evenly chopped.
Stir in sugar to desired sweetness.
Mix well and refrigerate several hours before serving.
May be frozen.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
While pasta is cooking, heat butter in saucepan.
Add flour, salt and pepper. Cook a few minutes; slowly add broth.
Bring to a boil, simmer until slightly thickened.
Stir in cream, chicken and cheese. Heat butter and lemon juice in a skillet.
Saute mushrooms until juice cooks off, about 5 minutes.
Drain pasta.
Combine with cream mixture.
Place 1/2 in a shallow dish.
Spread mushrooms over pasta, reserving some for garnish.
Top with remainder. Sprinkle with cheese and reserved mushrooms.
Bake at 375° for 20 minuets or until bubbly.

title: rice and beans
directions: Warm oil in large pot (4 quart or more).
Add the onion, carrot and green pepper; cook for about 2 minutes, then add the oregano, black pepper, red pepper, tarragon, salt and cumin.
Stir, then add kidney beans and cook for about 5 minutes at low heat, stirring constantly.
Add the 4 cups of water; increase the heat to high and cook until the water boils.
Stir in the rice, tomato paste and chicken bouillon, then lower the heat to low and cook for about 40 minutes.
Stir to fluff rice after 20 minutes.
To ensure rice is done, stick a spoon into the rice.
If the spoon stays upright, the rice is done.
Serves 6.

title: fruit bowl cake(low-fat, low calorie and low sugar)
directions: Bake cake (no cholesterol) recipe.
Let cool good.
Crumble 1/2 of cake into a large bowl.
Chop 1 1/2 bananas in rounds.
Put on top of cake.
Chop 1/2 of the strawberries and put on top also. Chop 1/2 of peaches and add to top.
Add 1/2 of crushed pineapple (drained) to top.
Mix instant pudding and add on top of pineapple.
Then repeat the same steps for the next layer from all ingredients left.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread jalapeno cheese dip in a pie plate.
Layer sour cream next.
Layer onions, black olives, tomatoes and cover with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until cheese is melted.
May be microwaved.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese, dressing mix and mayonnaise together. Set aside. Break open crescent rolls and roll out onto 2 cookie sheets, do not separate. Bake at 350° for 10 - 15 minutes or until golden brown. Let cool; spread mixture onto crust; sprinkle vegetables on top. Refrigerate.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add 7-Up.
Cool.
Add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Put in large dish, approximately 9 x 13-inch and let set up.

title: white hot chili
directions: In a 12-quart pot, sear the beef and pork in 3 tablespoons of olive oil.
Add onions, bell peppers and celery.
Cook over high heat until tender.
During cooking, add the Port wine.
Once tender, add all the tomato products.
Bring to a boil.
Add the shallots, Habaneros, garlic, jalapenos and the beer.
Stir until well blended.
Add the remainder of the seasonings.
Cook, covered, for 2 hours, stirring occasionally, over low heat.
Add the kielbasi and simmer, uncovered, for 2 hours.
Serve with diced purple onions and grated Cheddar cheese.
Yields 1 gallon chili!

title: pineapple green pepper cheese ball
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients together, except for 1/2 cup of pecans. Form into ball; roll in reserved pecans. Refrigerate until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: billie's custard pie
directions: Stir eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Pour in milk.
Preheat oven at 425°.
Fill pie crusts and dust on nutmeg.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° and bake 30 minutes longer.
A knife blade can be inserted in center of pie and should be clean.

title: soap bubble solution
directions: You will need a small dish, a spoon and a wire coat hanger.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Boil stew meat until tender, then mix all other ingredients. Add salt to taste.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, cracker meal, onion, evaporated milk and salt.
Roll in flour.
Brown meatballs in oil.
Drain.
Simmer in sauce for 15 minutes.
To make sauce, drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Measure pineapple juice and water to make 1 c. liquid. Blend with cornstarch until smooth.
Stir in vinegar, brown sugar, soy sauce and lemon juice.
Cook until thickened.
Blend in green pepper and pimento.
Add pineapple.
Simmer 15 minutes with meatballs or sausage in.
Enjoy!

title: fancy brussels sprouts
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, bring water, parsley, sugar and salt to a boil. Add Brussels sprouts. Cover and simmer for 6-8 minutes or until tender; drain. Add water chestnuts and butter; heat through. This has 11 grams carbohydrate.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Mix ingredients and add chicken.
Marinate at least 1 hour or up to 24 hours.
Broil chicken 10 to 20 minutes on broiler tray far enough from heat to prevent marinade from caramelizing.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Mix flour, pepper, salt and garlic; dip chicken cutlets. Brown to a golden color in butter.
Put in a warm dish.

title: nut crust
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Press on bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in a 400° oven for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: onion cauliflower bake
directions: Cut cauliflower into bite-sized pieces.
Prepare creamed onions according to package directions:
In saucepan place 1 1/2 cups water, 2 tablespoons butter and the 2 packages of frozen onions. Cover and bring to boiling over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer covered for 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in cheese, almonds and parsley.
Place in casserole dish and top with onions.
Bake until done.

title: homemade chocolate pudding
directions: In saucepan, mix together the dry ingredients.
Add milk, butter and vanilla. Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens (must stir constantly so pudding will be smooth and not lumpy). Delicious when eaten warm.

title: gofer balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into small balls.
Dip in melted chocolate.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Put the chicken in a heavy boiler, add onion, celery, salt and pepper; cover with water and cook until the chicken is tender. Remove the chicken and let cool until you can debone.
Remove and discard the onion and celery.
Strain the stock. Heat chicken stock and butter to boiling. Add more salt and pepper if needed.
Add dumplings to boiling stock, cover and cook for 12 minutes at a low boil.
Warm the chicken in the microwave. Thicken stock with a mixture of cornstarch and water. Add chicken and mix well with cooked dumplings.

title: santa fe salad
directions: Pour dressing over combined beans, cucumber, cauliflower, green pepper and olives.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator 2 hours. Drain, reserving marinade.
Add vegetables to greens; toss lightly.
Serve with marinade.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix flour and beer with a fork.
Let stand for 3 hours or longer at room temperature.
Make rings out of onions.
Dip rings in batter and fry in 2 to 3 inches of oil.
Turn when brown. Drain.
Salt to taste.

title: geri deshazer's kraut and beer fudge cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately to egg mixture.
Stir in kraut. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: Brown beef.
Add all remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix cake as directed; add the oil.
Bake cake on greased cookie sheet with sides.
Cool.
Spread drained pineapple on cake. Mix pudding and milk; beat in cream cheese.
Spread over top of pineapple; spread Cool Whip on pudding.
Top with coconut. Refrigerate before cutting.

title: breaded hamburger steaks
directions: Mix hamburger, pepper and salt. Shape into 2 large patties. Dredge in flour (both sides). Fry in small amount of cooking oil. Makes nice brown crust.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.
Can be refrigerated up to 1 week.
Makes 1 1/2 cups which equals a 14 ounce can.

title: speedy lobster soup
directions: Melt butter in large stew pot over low heat; slowly stir in lobster.
Allow to heat completely.
Combine milk, cream of mushroom soup, parsley, salt and pepper; add to lobster in pan. Serve piping hot with browned bread cubes.

title: fancy green beans
directions: Drain liquid
from
beans,
reserving 1/4 cup.	Lightly brown bacon; drain on paper towel, reserving excess drippings. Saute onion in
bacon
drippings;
add
beans,
cup	bean liquid and sugar.	Chop
bacon and add to bean mixture.
Cook, uncovered, over
low
heat until liquid is absorbed.
Top with almonds. Yields 2 to 3 servings.

title: cornmeal pancakes
directions: Pour boiling water over cornmeal and stir until thick; add molasses and milk.
Beat in eggs.
Add remaining dry ingredients; stir in shortening.
Bake on an ungreased griddle.
Makes 10 cakes.

title: sausage swirls
directions: Separate rolls into 4 rectangles and spread with mustard. Spread with thin layer of sausage.
Roll and chill until ready to serve.
Thinly slice each roll (10 swirls to a roll).
Place slices on ungreased pan.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes. Serve hot.
Makes 80 swirls.

title: stove top beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Cook onion and green pepper in drippings until tender; drain.
Add remaining ingredients except bacon and simmer for 30 minutes.
Before serving, crumble bacon and garnish top of beans.

title: new orleans pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients; bring to soft ball stage (238° to 240°), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir until mixture thickens, becomes creamy and cloudy and pecans stay suspended in mixture (be patient!).
Spoon out on buttered aluminum foil or parchment paper.
Let cool.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Set aside 1 cup cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix, 1/2 cup margarine, melted and cooled and 1 egg.
Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread mixture in pan.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, milk and Marshmallow Creme in 2-quart glass bowl.
Microwave on High 3 minutes.
Stir well.
Continue to microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes or until mixture boils. Microwave on medium and boil 5 minutes.
Reduce power if candy starts to boil over.
Mixture should be light almond color.
Add chocolate chips and chocolate squares; stir until melted.
Add vanilla. Fold in nuts and turn mixture into a buttered 8-inch square pan. Cool before cutting into squares.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: grilled teriyaki steak
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour over meat.
Marinate in refrigerator 4 to 5 hours.
Grill to desired doneness.

title: luscious lemon bar cookies
directions: Make crust of butter, salt, 2 cups flour and powdered sugar. Press firmly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until nicely browned.
Make filling by combining 1/4 cup flour and sugar.
Mix in beaten eggs and lemon juice.
Pour onto slightly cooled crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until set. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cool.
Cut into bars and serve.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package in salted water.
Arrange stalks in greased 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Layer chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter. Sprinkle all over dish.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until heated.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: In a casserole dish, layer beans, meat, guacamole dip, sour cream, cheese, onions and olives; put in the refrigerator for 20 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: greek shrimp saute(makes 4 servings)
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, combine margarine and oil.
Heat until margarine is melted.
Add shrimp, scallions and garlic. Saute over medium heat, stirring frequently until shrimp turns pink, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: scarlet sipper
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir gently and serve immediately. Yield:
4 cups (98 calories per 1 cup serving).

title: french onion soup
directions: In large skillet or slow cooking pot with browning unit, cook onions in butter until lightly browned.
In crock-pot, combine browned onions in butter with bouillon, water, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Cover and cook on low, 4 to 6 hours.
Top each bowl with toasted French bread sprinkled with cheese.
Makes 4 servings. Recipe may be doubled.
Keep hot in slow cooking pot and serve from pot.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Crumble crackers into crumbs (food processor works well).
Put cherries and pecans in crumbs.
Melt butter and marshmallows.
As soon as melted, stir all ingredients together.
Pack into wax paper lined box.
Freeze.
Slice to serve.

title: christmas sausage
directions: Mix seasonings with Madeira and water.
Add mixture to meat, mixing thoroughly with hands.
Form into patties and let stand for 24 hours.
To cook, place patties in large skillet.
Add enough water to barely cover bottom of pan.
Cover and cook for 2 minutes. Drain.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat until patties are browned and meat is completely done.
Does not freeze well!

title: baked vegetable casserole italiano(low cal)
directions: Combine vegetables in a casserole dish.
Stir in seasonings and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 375° oven. Serves 6.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine
peanut
butter,
ounces
Cool
Whip and ice cream. Pour into pie shells.
Top with 4 ounces Cool Whip and put in freezer.
Let set up before serving.

title: peanut butter creams
directions: Pour peanut butter and marshmallow cream in bowl.
Cook sugar and milk until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and pour over peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Beat until smooth and pour into buttered pan.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Stir in meat and brown.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook five minutes.
Stir in soup.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve on rice or buttered noodles. Garnish with parsley.

title: "punchy" bowl
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Divide in 1/2 (this recipe makes 2 bowls) for one bowl.

title: angel hash
directions: Mix together with mixer.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Can be frozen or place in a graham cracker pie crust.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: taco ring
directions: Brown meat and salt and pepper to taste. Add taco mix and stir. Mix shredded cheese to browned meat. Separate crescent rolls into triangles. In 14-inch round flat pan, place crescent rolls with points out forming a circle. Place meat mixture on crescent rolls and bring points of crescents to the center. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice and cool.
Cook chicken in small amount of water with onion, carrot, celery, salt and pepper.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Remove from pan and set aside.
In same pan, add flour, liquid and remaining butter and make a white sauce.
Add salt and pepper.
Combine all ingredients.
Top with buttered bread crumbs, cover and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown onion and sausage in skillet. Drain noodles. Add soups and milk to noodles. Combine with sausage and mix.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; form into loaf.
Bake in a 375° oven.

title: jack pot casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion; cook until golden.
Add tomato soup, and water noodles.	Cook until noodles are tender, stirring frequently.
Season to taste with pepper.
Add corn, olives and 1/2 cup grated cheese.	Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pasta & slaw salad
directions: Add cooked pasta to slaw, peas and dressing.
Enjoy.

title: shrimp
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pour over shrimp and bring to a boil.
Simmer with lid until shrimp is done (about 20 minutes).

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: Prepare rice as directed.
Cook onion in margarine (do not brown).
Remove from heat and stir in flour.
Add the 1 1/2 cups chicken broth.
Add cream.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add wild rice, mushrooms, chicken and pimento.

title: quick chicken
directions: In a large, deep skillet, melt butter.
Add garlic, onion, celery, green pepper and chicken.
Cook over medium heat until chicken is brown and vegetables have softened.
Add cream of celery and cream of mushroom soups.
Add 2 soup cans of milk or water; stir.

title: asparagus
directions: Clean asparagus; cut in 1-inch pieces. Cook 5 minutes in microwave. Let cool. Then mix other ingredients. Place in fridge. Serve cold.

title: chinese chicken
directions: In saucepan, cook green pepper and celery in butter until crisp-tender.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Add chicken and chop suey vegetables.
Heat through.
Serve with hot cooked rice. Pass the soy sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift and combine all dry ingredients together; set aside.
Mix oil, eggs and vanilla well.
Add all dry ingredients; mix well. Add zucchini and walnuts.
Butter and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana nut bread(1 loaf)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; combine remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Pour into prepared bread pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake about 55 minutes; cool on rack before slicing.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a greased 9-inch square pan. Place apple slices in pan. Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly. Sprinkle over apples. Bake 30 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown. Serve warm and with ice cream.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar and shortening.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time.
Mix and add buttermilk and soda.
Sift together and add flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice. Save small amount to dredge fruit and nuts.
May soak the fruit and nuts overnight. Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 300 degrees about 15 minutes.
Do not cook until brown.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and lemon extract until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients.
Combine jam and sour cream.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Divide into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Can be baked in 5 little pans or 3 medium pans.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 5 minutes.
Gradually mix in granulated sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Spread in greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with nuts.
Bake 13 minutes at 375°.
Bake on second shelf level from top.
Turn out onto towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar. Start rolling at small end, towel and cake together.
Cool. Unroll and spread with filling.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl with melted butter. Turn into greased casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tropical crunch snack mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Store in an airtight container.
Yield: 11 cups.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; let stand 20 minutes until it gets cold.
Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla together. Add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and chopped nuts to oat mixture. Mix all together and pour into a 9 x 13 x 1-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef, then put in large pot.
Chop the onion and chili peppers, adding them to the ground beef.
Add rest of the ingredients and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.

title: natural iron supplement
directions: Stick the nails in the apple.
The next day take the nails out and eat the apple.
Some of the iron in the nails will have gotten into the apple and will be used by your body.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Stir in milk, shortening and nuts.
Spread in 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar and cocoa.
Pour hot water over entire batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: twinky cake
directions: Prepare the cake according to directions and cook in a 9 x 13-inch wax paper lined pan.
Turn the cake onto a cookie sheet after cooled.
Cook the milk with the flour, stirring constantly, until boiled and thick (like paste).
Cool.
Beat the vanilla, sugar, salt, Crisco and oleo until very light and fluffy.
Add paste to this; beat until very smooth.
Split cake and put this between the layers.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Husk tomatillos, seed jalapenos and cook together in boiling water until tomatillos change color and peppers become slightly tender; drain.
Place in blender with remaining ingredients.
Use over beef enchiladas.

title: hanky pankies
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef; drain off grease.
Add cheese (cut-up) and melt over meat.
After cheese melts, add spices and stir well.
Spread thinly on party rye bread.
Put on cookie sheet and brown under broiler or in oven at 350° for approximately 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Great for parties!

title: mother's carrot-apple-raisin salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine carrots, apples and raisins.
In small bowl, add lemon juice to mayonnaise, then add to carrot mixture.
Stir gently to mix well.
After well-coated, cover and chill for 2 to 24 hours before serving.
If it seems too thick, stir in a little milk.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers,
onions
and
salt. Cover with water and stand overnight;
drain.
Make
a syrup of sugar, vinegar, white mustard
seed,
celery
seed and turmeric powder.
Bring syrup to a boil and add the cucumbers.
Cook 15 minutes.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and cut tomatoes in 1/2-inch slices.
Salt and pepper. Sprinkle onion salt on slices.
Cover in flour one at a time.
Put 1 1/2 cups of oil in frypan on medium-high heat.
Fry tomatoes, turning once.
Brown lightly.
Drain on paper towel or brown paper bag.

title: dill garlic pretzels
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Put 2 bags of pretzel wedges in pan and put mixture over.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.

title: sugar-free banana coconut custard
directions: Blend eggs and bananas until smooth in a blender.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Pour into six (8 ounce) custard cups.
Sprinkle with additional nutmeg and place in a large baking pan with 1-inch of hot water in it.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until custard has set.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: veggie squares
directions: Note:
Any raw vegetables may be added or substituted.

title: toll house pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar. Blend in butter.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Pour into shell.
Bake one hour in a 325° oven.
Serve warm with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: that apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg in a large bowl.
Add eggs, butter and vanilla extract then fold in the apples.
Pour mixture into pie crusts and bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes more or until done.
COOL COMPLETELY and serve.
Yield:
12 to 16 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: You will need an 8-inch square cake dish or pan.

title: mom's fried bread
directions: Heat oil until hot.
Drop pistolettes in, one at a time.
Turn each one until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.

title: bobbie's punch
directions: Add boiling water to jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cold water to juices.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Serves 35 to 40.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix butter and sugar, add vanilla, then add flour.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 300 degrees until brown.
Let cool for a few minutes, then roll in confectioners sugar.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Make a well and add the remaining liquid ingredients into the center of the bowl.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot baked fruit
directions: Combine last 4 ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Layer fruit as listed.
Pour sauce over fruit and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: huntington chicken
directions: In a 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole, combine all ingredients except cheese.
Cook, covered, 15 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Stir in cheese.
Serves 6.

title: tuna dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer until well blended. On sheet of wax paper, spread a little parsley.
Put mixture on top and roll it up in wax paper.
Keep in refrigerator.
This recipe tastes better if it is made a day before you need it.

title: orange and red onion salad
directions: In a skillet, melt margarine over medium heat.
Saute almonds until golden brown.
Remove almonds to paper towel to drain. Combine next 5 ingredients.
Beat in oil.
Combine lettuce, oranges, onion and almonds.
Toss with dressing.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: larry's chicken
directions: Combine ingredients in large container.
Cook on low until potatoes and carrots are tender.
Add more tomato juice or water if more liquid is desired.
Makes a large quantity; freezes well.

title: the big sweet(sweet potato pie)
directions: Cook the potatoes with skins on in boiling water for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
After boiling, cut ends off about 1/2 inch on each side.
Peel and cut potatoes lengthwise into strips.
While potatoes are still hot, put in bowl and add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Add just enough milk to make mixture stiff when stirring.
Put mixture in pie crust (make your own).
Bake at 320° to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until pie crust is done.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Beat sugars, oil, eggs and vanilla until very smooth.
Sift flour together with soda and salt.
Add to the sugar mixture.
Then add oatmeal and crushed cereal.
Roll in balls or drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.

title: apple crunch
directions: Pat in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan 3/4 of the flour, brown sugar and 1 stick of melted butter.
Cover with apple slices. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon.
Cover with the remaining crust mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy peach ice cream
directions: Mix peaches and sugar together in a blender.
Add to other ingredients.
Churn in ice cream maker according to manufacturer's directions.
Yields 4 quarts.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Salt cukes and onion; cover with ice for 3 hours.
Rinse well. Add to hot mixture.
Bring almost to boil; pack in jars and seal.

title: fruit sorbet
directions: Put berries through a fine sieve to get rid of seeds.
Mix all ingredients in a blender.
Pour into a metal bowl and place in freezer.
Remove from freezer 2 or 3 times during the freezing process and blend it again each time.
Then freeze completely until ready to serve.
Serve with either white chocolate mousse or chocolate mousse.

title: mexican rice
directions: Place prepared rice in a lightly buttered baking dish.
Spread chili over rice and top with onion; spread over all.
Top with cheese; sprinkle chili powder according to taste.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: susie's chocolate cake
directions: Dissolve cocoa in hot water.
Combine all other ingredients and mix well.
Add cocoa mixture last and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt in a double boiler, caramels and condensed milk.
Add pecans and dip in chocolate.
Dip tablespoons.
(Can put caramel, etc., in refrigerator until hard, then dip.)

title: vegetable breakaway bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Dip each piece in margarine. Layer 1/3 of biscuits in lightly greased 10-inch Bundt pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 the bacon, cheeses, onion and peppers.
Repeat the layers until all ingredients are used, ending with the biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: sliced pancake soup(frittatensuppe)
directions: Make a smooth paste of the cold milk and flour.
Stir in the egg and salt.
Heat enough fat in an omelette pan to cover the bottom of the pan; spoon into the pan enough batter to cover the bottom thinly and evenly.
Fry until crisp on both sides.
Add more fat before frying each pancake.
When cold, the pancakes are rolled up individually and cut into thin strips.
Add to hot beef broth.

title: economical chocolate pudding(self-saucing)
directions: Cream the butter and 1/2 cup of sugar with a few drops of vanilla essence until very light.
Add eggs, one at a time, and fold in the flour, 2 spoons cocoa and milk.
Grease an ovenproof dish and empty the mixture into the dish.
Sprinkle the mixture with the extra sugar and cocoa.
Gently pour on the hot water. Bake in moderate oven for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix altogether.
Put in baked pie crust or vanilla crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Overcook broccoli.
Drain and set aside.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add soup and cheese, cut in pieces.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add other ingredients and broccoli.
Cook until heated completely.
Serve hot with crackers or tortilla chips.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour and 2 tsp. salt.
Gradually stir in pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thickened.
Add lemon juice.
Cool mixture to room temperature. Bring water, salt, and oil to a boil.
Add acini de pepe.
Cook at rolling boil until done.
Drain, rinse with water, drain and rinse again.
Cool to room temperature.
Combine egg mixture and pasta and mix lightly but thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight in airtight container.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until chilled. May refrigerate as long as a week.
May also be frozen.
Makes 25 servings.

title: mom's beans
directions: Brown bacon and set aside.
Brown onion and drain.
Drain kidney beans and lima beans.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in preheated oven at 450° until brown.
Brush with melted margarine mixed with garlic when you take out of the oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan, that has been greased or sprayed with Pam.
Place chicken on top.
Pour oleo over chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: spiced cranberry punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat, cool and strain.
To serve, combine sugar mixture, fruit juices and ginger ale in a large punch bowl.
Yield:
7 quarts.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Blend squash.
Add seasonings.
Beat eggs and add evaporated milk. Mix all ingredients and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shells.
Bake in a preheated oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake additional 35 to 40 minutes or when knife is inserted and comes out cleaned.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except club soda and rum and mix well.
Then add club soda and rum.
Chill.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: In food processor bowl with metal blade or blender container, combine all ingredients.
Cover; process 30 seconds or, if using blender, stir after 15
seconds.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight to blend flavors.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: pizza burger
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Let stand.
Cook ground beef and drain.
Mix meat and sauce.

title: lime salad
directions: Prepare gelatin as directed on package; let set slightly. Have cream cheese at room temperature; whip until creamy.
Mix topping mix as directed on package; add to cream cheese and mix well.
Drain pineapple.
When gelatin begins to thicken, add cream cheese and topping mixture.
Fold in pineapple and pecans. Completely congeal.
Cut into squares; serve plain or on lettuce. Yields 12 servings.

title: crispy scalloped corn
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Top with Rice Krispies and melted butter. Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° about 60 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Heat griddle to 350°.
Shred potatoes to make 4 cups; drain. Mix with other ingredients.
Serve with applesauce.

title: cathedral window cookies
directions: Slowly melt butter and chocolate chips.
Remove from heat and add eggs and nuts.
Cool.
Add marshmallows in 2 to 3 additions. Mix well.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar on 3 pieces of waxed paper. Place mixture on the waxed paper and form into 3 rolls using some confectioners sugar on hands and on top.
Chill a few hours or overnight.
Slice and serve.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Use more or less flour to make cookie batter for drop cookies. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
These cookies will not brown easily.
Watch carefully for burning.

title: grandma warnken's candy clusters
directions: Melt bark over hot water.
Remove and add cereal and nuts. Wait 5 minutes, then add marshmallows.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.

title: tuna roll
directions: Drain tuna.
Mix together with softened cream cheese. Add pecans and onions.
Roll into ball. Garnish with parsley.
Serve with Town House crackers.

title: crab salad
directions: Dissolve
gelatine in
water;
heat
soup
and	add
to water. Blend in cream cheese, mayonnaise and rest of ingredients.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.	Serve with crackers.

title: easy garlic cheddar biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients just until moistened.
Drop 12 spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450 degrees until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: cajun spiced chicken
directions: Combine vegetable juice, vinegar, hot sauce, oregano and minced garlic in a large shallow container; stir well.
Add chicken, turning once to coat.
Marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Remove from marinade, reserving marinade.
Place chicken on microwave glass platter; cover with plastic wrap, turning back 1 corner to vent.
Microwave at High 8 to 10 minutes or until chicken is done, giving dish a quarter turn at 2 minute intervals. Let chicken stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Combine celery, pepper and onion in a 1-quart glass measure; microwave at High 3 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Combine reserved marinade and cornstarch, stirring until smooth.
Add to vegetable mixture and microwave, uncovered, at High 1 to 2 minutes or until thickened.
Serve chicken over rice; top with sauce.
Contains about 272 calories per chicken piece and 1/2 cup rice.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: pork and beans
directions: Buy one can of pork and beans and take it home.
Open the can. Pour beans into a pan; heat them.
Take the beans out of the pan and put them in a bowl.
Eat them carefully because they are hot.

title: sausage balls
directions: Fry sausage and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Make into balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: black midnight cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan or two 9-inch or three 8-inch round layer pans.
Measure all ingredients into a large mixer bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pan(s).
Bake in oblong pan about 45 minutes or layers for 30 to 35 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
If desired, frost cake.

title: 1,2,3 fudge
directions: Stir margarine and peanut butter together.
Add sifted powdered sugar, may not need quite all.
Put into greased 10 X 18 pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread evenly over fudge.
Let sit for several hours to cool; then cut into squares.
Note:
May be frozen until needed.

title: ri's chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles in chicken broth and drain.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients, except for cheese.
Shred 1/2 cheese onto mixture.
Cut remaining half of cheese in thick slices.
Pour mixture into 9 or 6-inch casserole pans. Top with cheese slices. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes covered with foil.
Serves 6.

title: easy water-whip pastry(double crust)
directions: Put Crisco in bowl.
Add boiling water and milk.
Beat mixture with fork until smooth and thick.
Sift flour and salt into mixture.
Stir with round the bowl strokes until dough clings together and cleans bowl.
Form into 2 balls.
Roll out on lightly floured board.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: memphis goulash
directions: Add all ingredients.
Simmer about 20 minutes.

title: jean's tomato florentine soup
directions: Add all items (except macaroni).
Bring to boil, then simmer for 30 minutes; add shell macaroni and simmer until tender.
Add water if you like a thinner soup or 1 1/2 cups of shell macaroni instead of 2 cups.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Beat shortening and peanut butter. Add sugar and brown sugar. Beat well. Add egg, milk and vanilla. Stir together flour, baking soda and salt. Gradually add to peanut butter mix. Shape dough into balls. Roll in sugar. Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from oven and place Kisses on top of each cookie.

title: vegetable medley casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, soup, cheese and yogurt; pour in 1-quart casserole.
Top with croutons.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers thin.
Chop onions and bell peppers and combine with cucumbers.
Add salt and let stand 3 hours; drain. Combine vinegar and sugar.
Add spices and bring to a boil.
Add drained cucumbers and heat, but do not boil.
Pack in jars and seal at once.

title: caramel pie filling
directions: Stir water, brown sugar and butter over heat.
Boil until mixture threads when dropped from a spoon.
Add cream, water and egg yolks to syrup.
Mix thoroughly.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Pour in baked pie crust.
