Cover with meringue made with whites of eggs.
Brown meringue at 300°.

title: diabetic shake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and mix at high speed. Result will be a 12 oz. shake.
Less than 100 calories.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift first five ingredients into ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan. Add rest of ingredients and stir till smooth. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. This cake is made without eggs.

title: elegant seafood rings
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Unroll dough; separate into strips.
Twist 2 breadsticks together; form into a ring, pinching edges to seal. Repeat with remaining breadsticks.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 18 to 22 minutes.
Keep warm.

title: dirty rice
directions: Boil the liver and gizzards in a pot of water with the bouillon cubes until tender.
When cool, chop the meat into small pieces and save the liquid.
Cook the rice with a little less water than you usually use, being careful not to overcook.

title: chicken olivia
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter, corn flakes and almonds. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
In frying pan, melt butter.
Sprinkle corn flake crumbs and almonds in butter.
Stir and sizzle for a few minutes.
Spoon evenly over casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: desserts from the grill
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup of juice and 6
pineapple slices.
Save remaining juice and pineapple for another use.
In a microwave dish, combine butter, brown sugar, vanilla, spices and reserved pineapple juice.
Microwave, uncovered, on high for 1-2 minutes or until bubbly.
Brush half of the mixture on both sides of the pineapple rings and cake slices.
On an uncovered grill, over medium heat, cook pineapple and cake for 1-2 minutes on each side or until lightly browned, brushing occasionally with pineapple mixture.
Place slices of cake on a plate, top with a pineapple slice, add ice cream and drizzle with the caramel sauce.

title: snap beans
directions: Place cubed salt meat in pot with water;
boil for about 1/2 an hour.
In another pot, add 2 or 3 cans snap beans or fresh beans.
Add salt meat, onion, and oil.
Add Tabasco Sauce.
Cook until done.

title: granny's holiday dressing
directions: Bake cornbread according to directions on box.	Crumble cornbread.	Toast hamburger buns in little pieces until a little brown.
Combine the cornbread and toasted buns.
Mix well.	Add broth.
Be sure mixture is really moist.
Add the mushroom and celery soups.
Add water chestnuts, onions, celery.
Mix all well. Add the well beaten eggs, and mix again.
Place in a large pan and refrigerate overnight to be sure all ingredients are saturated.	It will be very moist.	Cook in preheated oven at 375° for 1 hour.
Slice and serve with a big spoon.

title: banana pudding
directions: In medium bowl mix, pudding mix with 2 cups of cold milk.
Let stand.
Add sour cream and cool whip, mixing well.
Place in layers into another bowl a layers of bananas, layer of vanilla wafers, and a layer of pudding.
Continue this process until bananas, wafers, and pudding is all used up.
Ending with pudding on top.

title: end of garden pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers, tomatoes, cabbage, peppers and onions in 1/2 cup salt and two quarts of water overnight.
Drain well.
Cook carrots, beans and celery until tender.
Drain well.
Mix with remaining vegetables, mustard seed, celery seed, turmeric, sugar and vinegar; boil for 10 minutes.
Pack in sterile jars and seal.

title: shells
directions: Cook shells according to box directions; drain (do not rinse). In same pot, put margarine and shells.
Cut up tomatoes into bite-sized pieces and put them along with juice from cans into the pot.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil and then cover and cook over medium heat for about 30 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Cream chili sauce and cream cheese and add crabmeat, well drained.
Add onion and mayonnaise; chill well and serve.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix together vinegar, water and oil.
Heat, then dissolve sugar in the mixture.

title: world lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles per package directions, flexible.
Cool in cold water.
Brown ground beef.
Add green bell pepper, Ragu marinara sauce, sliced olives and Ricotta cheese.
Mix well.
The sauce should not be real thin.
Begin layering with 4 noodles, 1/4 cup of sauce and 2 hard-boiled eggs, sliced.
Add 1/3 each of the cheeses.
Spread over layer.
Second and third layer do the same way as the first layer.
Fourth layer, just cover the noodles with sauce.

title: yum yum pie
directions: Crust: Melt margarine in pan. Take off heat and mix flour and nuts. Place in oblong pan and bake at 350° until golden brown. Cool completely.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and broccoli in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Crumble and brown meat in skillet.
Add to all other ingredients in 5-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium flame for approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until desired thickness is achieved.
Serve with warm cornbread or tortilla chips.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in a heavy skillet and cook until peanuts pop like popcorn.
Put in soda.
Beat and pour up.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine, adding gradually the sugar.
Blend in eggs (1 at a time) and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Alternate milk and dry ingredients, beating at medium speed, until well blended and is smooth and creamy.
(Will be very thick.)
Pour into a Pammed tube pan and bake in 350° oven for 60 to 65 minutes.
Turn cake out immediately onto cake plate and spread with stick of margarine or butter until outside is coated and soft.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar with a touch of cinnamon.

title: french pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add milk and eggs.
Pour thin layer of batter in a medium heated buttered skillet.
Lightly brown on both sides.
While warm, spread butter and sprinkle powdered sugar on pancake.
Roll up the pancake and butter and sugar the top.

title: sprouted wheat bread
directions: Drain and rinse twice daily until sprouts are as long as the grain kernel (about 2 days).
Do not rinse the day you make the bread.
Put sprouted wheat through a food grinder or Champion juicer.
You may add ground or chopped dried fruits such as raisins, dates or apples.
Spray loaf pan with a generous amount of Pam and sprinkle with cornmeal as bread makes a sticky syrup as it bakes and is hard to get off a baking pan.
Dampen hands with water and put bread into pan.
Put all equipment into water to soak immediately as otherwise it will be difficult to clean. Bread does not rise.
Bake at 175° for 2 to 3 hours.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together the oil and sugar. Add the eggs. Beat well. Add remaining dry ingredients, alternating with buttermilk as needed. Add vanilla, apples and pecans. Mix well and pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°. (Can use Pam spray.)

title: busy day spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in very little oil until tender; add meat and brown slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly until thick, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Mix Jell-O, water and strawberries and refrigerate until thick.
Add pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Mix and put in ungreased 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8
minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Mix and spread over pretzel mix.
Spoon Jell-O mixture over.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.

title: diabetic pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and pineapple together.
Whip D-Zerta whipped topping according to directions.
Add Sugar Twin and lemon juice.
Fold in cream cheese and pineapple.
Pour in graham cracker crust or regular pie shell.
Let set for 3 to 4 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: green tomato relish
directions: You will also need sterilized jars.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Do not grease pan.
Put half of crumbs in bottom of pan.
Pour two cans of any Thank You filling over first layer.
Top with rest of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix and bake in an 8-inch pie tin at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve hot with chips or crackers.
May put chopped nuts on top.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Mix corn bread; bake at 425°.
Stir-fry ground meat in a large Pammed skillet.
When meat is done, add chopped eggplant, chopped onion, chopped jalapeno pepper, Creole seasoning and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer together until vegetables are done. Combine with cooked corn bread.
Add enough water to moisten.
Bake at 375° in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish until brown.

title: blueberry or mincemeat pie variation
directions: In small mixing bowl blend all the above, set aside. Fill pie shell approximately 3/4 full, drop by spoonfuls bowl mixture. Take a butter knife and cut into the filling swirling cream mixture into pie filling. Bake as usual.

title: date sticks
directions: Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cut into strips and roll in powdered sugar (2 1/2 x 3/4-inch).

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hands.
Pat out into a loaf pan.
Cover
with
Piquant Sauce and bake about 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: bacon and water chestnuts
directions: Slice bacon strips into thirds.
Wrap around 1 water chestnut and secure with a toothpick.
Broil until bacon is crisp.
Serve with cocktail sauce or teriyaki sauce, mixed with sugar to taste.

title: brother's pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add corn syrup and mix well.
Beat in eggs.
Mix in vanilla, salt and pecans.
Bake at 345° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vicki's sauerkraut and meatball casserole
directions: *I blend my tomatoes into a juice.

title: cucumber pickles aristocrats
directions: Slice pickles to 1/4-inch thick.
Make brine of water and salt to float an egg.
Let stand in brine for 7 days, stirring each day.
Drain.
Cover with water which contains alm the size of an egg.
Boil 10 minutes.
Drain.
Cover with water which contains ginger.
Boil 10 minutes.
Drain.
Simmer for 1/2 hour in vinegar, water, celery seed, white sugar, salt and green cake coloring to suit color.
Mix whole cloves, bark cinnamon and mixed spices. Seal while hot.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant and soak in cold salted water for 30 minutes.
Drain and cook until tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain again.
Add all ingredients, place in baking dish and top with additional grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cornmeal muffins
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and eggs.
Beat until thick and light colored.
Stir in alternately flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt with the milk.
Mix thoroughly and bake about 20 minutes at 400° in well-buttered muffin pans.
Yields 14 to 16 muffins.

title: pork chops and rice(heritage recipe)
directions: Mix rice, water, celery soup and mushroom soup.
Put into greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Lay pork chops uncooked on top of all.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add sugar and can milk.
Stir well.
Add vanilla flavoring, then add milk.
Pour into ice cream churn.

title: mystery bars
directions: Cream butter and
cup
sugar.
Add 1 cup flour and mix to crumbly mass.
Pat evenly into 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: deluxe mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add sour cream and cream cheese. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Smooth top of potatoes. May cover with bread crumbs and a little melted butter.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 minutes.
This dish may be frozen or refrigerated for later use, but must be cooked longer.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place apple slices in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together thoroughly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is a golden brown.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: pecan roll cookie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in vanilla and almond flavorings. Add flour slowly; now add chopped pecans.
Shape small portions of dough into rolls about 2-inches long and 1/2-inch in diameter. Press a pecan half on top of each roll.
Bake on buttered cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
While hot, sprinkle lightly with confectioners sugar.

title: lemon creme bars
directions: In large glass bowl, melt butter 1-1/2 to 2 minutes.
Combine oats, frosting mix, flour and baking powder with butter.
Mix until crumbly.
Press 2/3 mixture into glass cake pan.
Combine condensed milk, peel and juice.
Pour over crust, sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Cook on SIMMER for 7 minutes and HIGH for 3-4 minutes.
Cool and serve.
Better after refrigeration.

title: sauteed shrimp
directions: Boil shrimp until pink.
Clean them and remove tails.
Saute in skillet with Italian dressing.
Add salt and pepper and squeeze fresh lemon juice onto the shrimp.
Serve over your favorite pasta noodles or saute fresh zucchini and yellow squash slices with the shrimp.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Boil breasts until done (approximately 40 minutes). Remove skin and bones. Cut into large chunks.
Lay chicken in a 9 1/2 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice together. Lay broccoli over chicken. Top with soup mixture. Sprinkle with grated cheese and top with crumbs.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: rice hot dish
directions: In Dutch oven, brown hamburger and onions.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Add remaining ingredients except chow mein noodles.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chow mein noodles. Return to oven for 1/2 hour longer.

title: southwestern rice and bean salad
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: *This is optional; I don't include this ingredient.

title: stewed tomato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Toss bread stuffing with butter.
In a 2-quart casserole, combine tomatoes, sugar, salt, pepper and basil.
Sprinkle with bread stuffing cubes.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini savories
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 325° about 25 minutes.
Cut into 48 pieces.

title: simple banana pudding
directions: Pour 3 cups milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix and beat until mixture begins to stiffen (about 2 minutes).
In separate 2-inch deep dish, place a layer of vanilla wafers on bottom and sides of dish.
Chip 1 1/2 bananas over wafers.
Then cover with 1/2 of vanilla pudding.
Cover with vanilla wafers.
Repeat with bananas and pudding.
Finally, cover with a layer of vanilla wafers. Refrigerate for several hours.

title: chess cakes
directions: Melt on low heat oleo and brown sugar.
Remove from heat; put in mixing bowl and beat in (in this order) sugar, eggs (one at a time), flour, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 300° oven 40 to 50 minutes or until it tests done.
Cut into bars while warm and roll in powdered sugar. Keeps well in airtight container.

title: hasenpfeffer(wild game)
directions: The ingredients mentioned can be varied to accommodate one or more rabbits.

title: granny's chicken and rice
directions: Add all ingredients together in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Cover and cook slow (300°) for 2 to 3 hours, adding water if needed.

title: 2-minute fudge
directions: In 1 1/2 quart casserole dish, stir sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla together until partially blended (mixture is too stiff to blend thoroughly).
Put butter over top in center of dish. Microwave for 2 minutes or until milk feels warm on bottom of dish.
If butter has not melted, it will when stirred.
I sometimes add a heaping tablespoon of peanut butter after microwaving.
Blend in nuts and pour in 8x4x3 dish.
Chill 1 hour or 20 to 30 minutes in freezer.
Makes 36 squares.

title: "easy zucchini bread"
directions: Mix in order.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: broccoli-cheez whiz rice casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli and place in a large mixing bowl with cream of mushroom soup and water.
Stir in Cheez Whiz and rice.
Add a dash of salt and pepper.
Cut margarine into chunks and distribute these.
Pour all into lightly oiled 2-quart casserole and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: canned peppers
directions: Bring water and vinegar to a boil.
Put peppers and optional cauliflower in hot jars.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour hot vinegar and water over peppers and seal jars.

title: quick fudge
directions: Heat chips and condensed milk in saucepan over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted. Remove from heat; blend in vanilla. Spread in buttered 8-inch saucepan. Chill until firm, at least 4 hours. Makes 36 pieces. Can be made in microwave.

title: easy shrimp dip
directions: Blend in blender shrimp cocktail and cream cheese with chives.

title: chicken 'n dumplings
directions: Mix 1 batch of biscuit dough.
Roll on floured board.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Drop into mixture (listed ingredients). Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Heat sweet potatoes in saucepan until hot.
Mash while hot and add sugar, butter, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg.
Mix.
Beat in milk and eggs. Whip well. Turn into greased 3-quart casserole.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello with hot water; add sour cream, blending well. Then add pineapple, coconut, mandarin oranges and pecans. Refrigerate until congealed.

title: caramels
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Add brown sugar and salt, stirring until thoroughly mixed.
Blend in corn syrup.
Add sweetened condensed milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir, over medium heat, until candy reaches firm ball stage (245°), 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cool thoroughly.
Cut into small squares.
Wrap each piece individually.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix pulp, sugar, cinnamon, soda, eggs, baking powder and butter.
Add milk and flour alternately to the mixture.
Mix well. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
When pudding is done, pour the following sauce over while still warm.
Nuts may be added to sauce, if desired.

title: stuffed jumbo shells with pourover sauce
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add seasoning and cheese.
Cool 5 minutes.
Stir in sauce.
Stuff cooked and drained jumbo shells.

title: ruth's cherry crisp
directions: Pour pie filling into a 9-inch pie plate.
With pastry blender cut butter into flour, brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake 10 minutes.
Serve cold with ice cream (very good, not too sweet).

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken pieces in Dutch oven. Salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle rice on top of chicken. Pour soups over rice and chicken. Add stick of margarine. Bake 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender at 350°.

title: veg-all beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
In 1 1/2-quart boiling water to which 1 1/2 teaspoons salt has been added, lightly brown the onion in margarine or butter.
Add ground beef and cook slowly until brown, about 10 minutes.
Blend in flour.
Add cooked noodles.
Add Veg-All, including the liquid, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Sift powdered sugar and cocoa together into mixing bowl.
Melt margarine and Velveeta (over medium heat) in saucepan until smooth (stir continuously).
Add margarine and Velveeta to powdered sugar and cocoa mixture.
Add vanilla.
Add nuts (if desired). Mix well.
Spread into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.

title: black-eyed peas supreme
directions: Cook peas until almost done. Add salt. Brown ground beef.
Add to peas along with onion, pepper and chili powder.
Cook until tender. Add okra and finish cooking. Serve over rice.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, vanilla and almond extract. Combine the flour, cream of tarter, baking soda, salt and nutmeg; gradually add to creamed mixture. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown. Cool on wire racks.

title: sausage balls
directions: Allow cheese and sausage to warm to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Shape into small balls, slightly larger than bite size.
Bake at 375° until browned.
Use cookie sheet with raised edges so fat doesn't run off!

title: pot roast beef
directions: Put roast in large baking pan.
Pour soup over.
Cut up in fourths.
Place vegetables after cleaning and cutting up.
Bake at 375° for 3 hours or until tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pistachio cream pie
directions: Combine pineapple, yogurt, pudding mix, and coconut. Mix well. Stir in Cool Whip. Blend well.
Spoon into baked pie crust. If desired, top with additional Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and cinnamon.
Add flour and mix well.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Mix well and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli into small pieces.
Slice mushrooms.
Mix sugar and vinegar separately.
Mix all ingredients together and chill at least 4 hours.

title: microwave lasagne
directions: Combine hamburger, spaghetti sauce and water.
In another bowl, combine cottage cheese, eggs and pepper.
Spoon 1 cup meat mixture in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Alternate layers of noodles, egg mixture, Mozzarella cheese, sauce, noodles, egg mixture, sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Heat, covered, 8 minutes on High. Continue cooking at 50% power for 30 to 32 minutes.
(Turn halfway through.)
Let stand, covered, for 15 minutes.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix lightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: captain soup
directions: Brown beef with onion, drain.
Add soups and V-8 juice and bring to boil.
Add vegetables and cook for 2 hours or longer.
If using slow cooker, cook on low for 8-10 hours.
Makes about 3 1/2- 4 quarts.

title: ham dill dip
directions: Blend all ingredients and serve in cut out bread or serve with crackers.

title: stuffed wild duck
directions: Drain sauerkraut well
and combine with bell pepper and onion. Stuff duck with mixture.
Wrap duck in foil and place, breast side
down,
in
baking
dish or pan.
(This keeps meat from being dry.)
Bake
in a 350° oven for 3 hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: grandmother's rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, salt and other ingredients except rice.
Strain scalded milk and pour all ingredients in buttered casserole, then add the rice and stir.
Place the casserole in a water bath and bake it at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples, pecans and sugar.
Let stand 1 hour. Add flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt and soda. Mix well and add to apple mixture. Stir vegetable oil, vanilla and beaten eggs.
Stir in drained cherries.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: mom's fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and margarine to soft ball stage, stirring constantly, about 30 minutes.
Test by dropping into cold water. Drops will form in water, but will be soft and will not hold shape when taken out.
If using candy thermometer, cook to soft ball marking.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli as directed on package. Drain well. Mix all ingredients in a greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Spread Cheez Whiz on top while hot.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain and chop fruit.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add lemonade and stir until melted.
Chill until slightly thickened. Blend in whipped topping and fold in fruits.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Unmold and slice. Makes 12 servings.

title: apple custard pie
directions: Arrange 1/2 of apples in bottom of 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Mix sugar and flour; spread 1/2 over apples.
Pour in remainder of apples and spread remainder of flour-sugar mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pat with butter and dash of nutmeg.
Pour milk, mixed with beaten egg and vanilla, over entire mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 50 minutes.

title: peach-apple pie
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan and simmer about 5 minutes.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with Streusel Crunch Topping.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Allow cheese to reach room temperature.
Combine in a mixer bowl and beat until well blended.
Add Worcestershire sauce, cayenne pepper, salt, onion powder and garlic powder.
Add 1/2 cup the chopped pecans.
Chill; shape into a ball and roll ball into remaining pecans.
Chill thoroughly.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pudding mix, Cool Whip and pineapple together.
Add marshmallows and nuts, mixing well.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: hungarian coffee cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients. Mix.
Put half of mixture into a greased angel food cake tin, then sprinkle nut mixture on top of mix.
Add the rest of the mix. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make brownies according to mix.
Bake brownies.
Let cool.
Meanwhile prepare mousse according to directions.
Break candy bars into small pieces in food processor. Break up brownies into small pieces and place half in bottom of large glass bowl or trifle dish.
Cover with half of mousse, then half of candy and then half of Cool Whip.
Repeat layers with the remaining ingredients.
Serves up to 24.

title: ricotta lemon nut bread
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, beat together remaining ingredients except pecans.
Add mixture to dry ingredients with pecans; stir just to blend.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: snow white soup
directions: Cook cauliflower and discard broth.
Make a roux with the butter and flour, then add to roux 1 pint milk and bay leaf and simmer 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf and blend cooked mixture, half of cauliflower, 1 pint cream or milk, salt and vegetable cubes until liquified.
Reheat and add the remainder of the cauliflower (finely chopped).
(Half the cauliflower is blended, half is chopped for texture.)
Garnish with cheese.
Serves 4.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat eggs; gradually add sugar.
Beat until creamy; add oil and blend well.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder together.
Gradually add to first mixture, beating well.
Fold in apples.
Pour into greased, floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Do not open door while baking.
Good with or without icing.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, margarine and chocolate chips over low heat in a saucepan.
Pour over cereal.
Mix together.
Add powdered sugar to mixture and continue mixing evenly.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky Way bars in saucepan with butter or margarine and pecans, then cool.
Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in cooled mixture.
Alternately add dry ingredients and liquid.
Bake in 4 greased and floured layer cake pans for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
When layers are cool, put together with icing.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and mayonnaise, then add hot water.
Add dry ingredients, all at once.
Pour in greased and floured (9 x 13-inch) pan and bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: twix bars
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with crackers.
Boil all other ingredients, except chocolate chips and peanut butter, for 5 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Top with another layer of crackers. Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter and pour over crackers. Refrigerate until set.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add chips and flour.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Mix in pecans and form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Bake on greased cookie sheet.

title: picante spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well, reserving 1/2 cup cooking liquid.
Cook onion in butter in large skillet until tender, about 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add flour and cook and stir until bubbly.
Gradually add reserved spinach liquid and milk.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir in cheese.
Cook and stir until cheese melts.
Stir in Pace picante sauce, drained spinach and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Combine softened margarine, sugar and syrup.
Add chocolate chips, nuts and stir in beaten eggs.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: pasta spaghetti carbonaralla
directions: Set aside butter, eggs and cheese in separate bowls at room temperature.
Mix cooked meats and cream; heat to simmer and keep warm.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
Put in heated serving bowl.
Stir in butter, parsley, pepper and cheese.
Stir in meat and cream mixture.
Stir in eggs.
Season with salt and pepper as needed. Serve with extra cheese.
Serves 4.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and melted butter.
Add beaten eggs and pecans to syrup mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake in oven at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Makes one (9-inch) pie.

title: chamolone(italian heavy pound cake)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix to form a soft dough-like biscotti.
Grease a tube or bundt pan.
Spoon mixture and bake at 325°
for 1 hour.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs.
Mix.
Add bananas; mix until smooth.
Add rest of dry ingredients, stirring until moist.
Stir in pecans.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to wire rack to finish cooling.

title: pork barbecue pie wagon style
directions: Cook good size pork roast in Dutch oven until it falls off bones.
Cool in broth.
Take meat out and chop to bite size; remove fat.
Add to pot tomato puree, chopped onions and bell peppers.
Add Louisiana hot sauce to taste and cook down.
Don't cook too dry; it is supposed to be juicy.
Add vinegar to taste. When at the right consistency, serve on buns with a fork.

title: so very easy cheese ball
directions: Combine Velveeta cheese and cream cheese in mixing bowl.
Beat at low speed until smooth.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped walnuts.
Chill in refrigerator until firm. You may shape into "Yule log" for the holidays.
Serve with crackers.
Yields 8 to 12 servings.

title: bird's nests
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add and beat in egg yolk, flour and vanilla.
Form in balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in slightly beaten egg white and then roll in chopped nuts.
Place on cookie sheet and indent in middle with thumb.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Remove and press again with thumb.
Bake 10 more minutes. While still warm, fill center with jelly or jam.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions, pour 1/2 of batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: honey lemon buttermilk dressing
directions: In a bowl whisk together zest, lemon juice and honey until combined well.
Whisk in buttermilk, yogurt, oil, vanilla and a pinch of salt.
Makes about 3/4 cup.

title: fried jam sandwiches
directions: Make a jam sandwich, then beat egg and milk to color.
Melt some margarine in an iron skillet.
Dip sandwich in egg mixture, coating both sides, then fry in butter.
May eat with syrup on top like French toast.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together oil, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, salt, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg, nuts and apples.
Batter will be very thick. Spoon into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Glaze, if desired.

title: deep dish taco squares(makes 6 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix baking mix and water; press into 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes.
Brown meat with green pepper and onion; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasonings. Spoon over meat mixture.
Top with paprika, if desired.
Bake 25 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes; cut into squares.

title: eggnog punch
directions: Let juice and strawberries partially thaw.
Pour eggnog into punch bowl.
Pour juice from can into punch bowl.
Beat with mixer.
Stir in strawberries.
Serve.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown onion and beef in skillet, drain well.
Mix cream cheese with soup.
Mix all ingredients except biscuits in casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Put biscuits on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown, uncovered.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Place 1 quart fresh strawberries in cooled pie shell.
Crush remaining berries in saucepan.
Add sugar, cornstarch and water, blending well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickens and boils.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add butter; stir until blended.
Strain mixture and cool.
Pour cooled glaze over berries in pie shell.
Chill about 3 hours.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: finger steak
directions: Slice steak into 1 x 2 1/2-inch strips.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Blend together egg and milk.
Dredge strips and cover completely with flour.
Fry in hot oil.

title: crunchy snack mix(makes 5 cups)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Store in covered container up to 1 month. When ready to serve, pour mixture into ice cream cones.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add other ingredients and add flour.
Drop cookies by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Press cookies flat with floured fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: viva-la-chicken
directions: Mix soups, milk, onion and salsa.
Butter flat pan (cake size) and layer tortilla chips, then 1/2 the chicken, then soup mixture, then cheeses.
Repeat layers and top with cheeses.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add egg slightly beaten.
Add flour, salt and baking powder sifted.
Add milk. Mix thoroughly.
Add raisins.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bake in moderate oven (350°).

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all together and set overnight in sealed container.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil; add soup, mayonnaise and sour cream. Add chicken and rice. Mix well. Pour in 9 x 13 inch greased baking dish. Cover with crushed cornflakes, about 1-1/2 cup. Drizzle with 1 stick melted butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend in blender until well blended.
Serve with fresh vegetables (celery, carrot sticks, cauliflower).

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Melt morsels and peanut butter in a double boiler.
Add Chinese noodles.
Dip on wax paper to cool.
Delicious!

title: idaho scallopini
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Peel potatoes and slice thin.
Toss with flour.
Alternate layers of potatoes and mushrooms in well buttered baking dish, sprinkling each layer with seasonings.
Pour in broth mixed with wine.
Cover and bake 45 minutes.
Uncover. Sprinkle with cheese and continue baking another 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: cornbread
directions: Put ingredients (except grease) in a bowl and stir, then add grease.
Put it in the black pan.
Put it in stove, hot hot hot (100°) for 90 minutes.
Take it out of stove.
Cut it with knife. Put aluminum foil over it.
Set it on counter.
When everything else is done we eat it.

title: pudding in a cloud
directions: Prepare pudding mix with milk as directed on package for pudding.
Place plastic wrap over surface and chill for about 3 hours.
Divide whipped topping among 6 dessert glasses (about 1/3 cup in each).

title: poached pears
directions: Peel and core pears.
Place in microwave-safe container.
Pour small amount of orange juice over each pear and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Wait until you are ready for dessert, then microwave until soft and serve with vanilla yogurt (optional) in individual dishes.
If you are not on a diet, serve with ice cream.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Combine ingredients as listed; pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Place in dish and add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Dissolve sugar, Karo, salt and water in medium cast-iron skillet, stirring until mixture begins to boil.
Turn heat down and stir occasionally.
Cook about 6 to 8 minutes.
Add peanuts, stirring occasionally.
Cook until syrup begins to brown and peanuts are parched.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Stir and cook 1 minute.
Add soda.
Stir fast and pour onto buttered foil.

title: molasses popcorn balls
directions: Pop about 2 1/2 or 3 quarts unsalted popcorn; mix with wooden spoon until completely coated.
Makes about 2 dozen balls.

title: party pizza appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients, except biscuits.
Separate each biscuit into 3 pieces.
Make them look like little pizza crust. Top with mixture.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Makes 90.

title: goblin guzzler
directions: You will need 4 (10 ounce) glasses.

title: fruit flavor pops
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water. Pour in paper cups or molds (at least 8).
Insert wooden spoons of popsicle sticks.

title: icebox vegetable salad
directions: Combine all vegetables in a large glass bowl.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cool slightly and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, oil and flour; mix well.
Grease muffin pan and fill half full with batter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Prepare one envelope soup mix as directed on package.
Add pork chops, carrots and potatoes.
Cook until vegetables are semi-tender.
Pour into ungreased casserole dish.
Prepare Bisquick as directed on package for dumplings.
Drop into hot casserole.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: Vary the amount of flour, depending upon whether you like a thick or thin batter.
Some add a little sugar to make the cakes browner.

title: mexican pasta salad
directions: In large salad bowl, add macaroni and vinegar.
Let stand while preparing other ingredients.
Add oil and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: butterballs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Work in flour, salt and nuts until dough holds together.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Crumble yeast; add 1/2 cup of warm water.
Wait 1 minute; then add salt, sugar, eggs, Crisco and cup of warm water.
Beat 2 minutes; add flour and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight; then make out, let rise and bake at 450°.

title: orange slice pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and lemon juice, beat well.
Add Cool Whip.
Fold in mandarin orange slices and nuts.
Pour into pie crusts and chill.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Mix and heat milk, soup, and cheese. Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
May top with onions.
Bake another 10 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Reduce heat; cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Add the carrots, potatoes and broccoli.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes, covered.
Add the cream of chicken soup, water and Velveeta cheese.
Heat just until cheese melts.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream together oleo, Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks (one at a time), buttermilk, soda and flour.
Add egg whites, coconut and nuts.
Bake in three layers at 350° until done.

title: ice cream chocolate sauce
directions: Save the juice from canned fruit, especially peaches.
Use it as a marinade and to baste the meat while cooking.

title: farmhouse barbecue muffins
directions: Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Flatten into 5-inch circles. Press each into the bottom and up the sides of a greased muffin cup.
Set Aside.
In a skillet, brown ground beef.
Drain. In a small bowl, mix ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar, and chili powder.
Stir until smooth.
Add to meat and mix well.
Divide the meat mixture among biscuit lined muffin cups.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 18-20 minutes or until golden brown. Cool for 5 minutes before removing from tin and serve.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt margarine in oven. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine; pour sweetened milk evenly over crumbs. Top with remaining ingredients; press down lightly. Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until lightly browned. Cool; cut into squares.

title: crab dip(serves 6)
directions: Mix all.
Place in a "Pam'd" Corning bowl.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes with a cover.
Take off cover and continue baking for 5 minutes.
Serve on Triscuits.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Toast pecans on a cookie sheet on middle rack of oven at 350° for 8 minutes.
Mix all other ingredients except pecans.
Bring to a boil and cook to soft ball stage.
Stir constantly being careful not to burn.
Remove from heat and add pecans; stir enough to coat with syrup.
Separate on waxed paper.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: tuna-chip salad
directions: Combine
lettuce,
vegetables
and
tuna in a bowl; mix well. Chill.
Add chips and enough mayonnaise to moisten just before serving; mix well.	Yields 6 servings.

title: paradise rice salad
directions: Cook rice; cover and chill.
Combine orange juice, bottled dressing, honey and orange peel.
Stir into rice.
Cover and chill. Drain spinach; chop celery and toast almonds.
Add along with oranges just before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut cookies
directions: Cream sugars and oleo.
Add eggs.
Mix in flour, oatmeal and baking powder.
Add peanuts last, mixing by hand.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Scramble hamburger in a skillet size baking dish.
Pour can of cream of chicken soup over meat.
Put Tater Tots on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: creole pork chops
directions: Put oil in iron skillet and brown seasoned pork chops.
Drain oil and return chops to skillet.
Add raw or cooked rice on top of pork chops.
Chop bell pepper and onion on the rice.
Pour can of tomatoes on top.
Put a lid on the skillet and simmer until chops are fork-tender.
Serve hot and enjoy.

title: jo's chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken with onion.
Let cool. Remove from bones and cut up.
Cook noodles and spaghetti in broth.
Make gravy of margarine, flour and broth.
Add mushroom soup, mushrooms and pimentos.
Cut up cheese on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a greased dish.
(You may also add 1 cup cooked rice and bread crumbs on top, if desired.)

title: macaroni salad
directions: Add salt to water and bring to a boil.
Add macaroni.
Boil until tender, 10-14 minutes.
Drain.
Add butter.
Mix to season and prevent macaroni from sticking together.
Add mayonnaise, vinegar, chopped eggs, onion, and pepper.
Let set 2 hours or overnight.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar very well until light and fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time and beat well between each egg addition.
Add a little flour at a time; add vanilla, juice and rind after first cup of flour.
Always beat well.
Pour into ungreased Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Combine and simmer for 1 hour the celery, carrots, onion, water and bouillon. Add noodles. Cook 15 minutes more. Add chicken. Cook 15 minutes more and serve.

title: sourdough pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; set aside.
Mix sourdough starter, egg, oil and buttermilk.
Mix dry ingredients into sourdough mixture when ready to use.
Spoon 1/4 cup on preheated grill and cook.
Makes 12 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: lo-cal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and baking soda in large bowl.
Mix together margarine, sweetener and egg.
Mix dry ingredients with applesauce.
Fold in Bran buds, raisins and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet by tablespoon.
Lightly flatten with fork (dipped in milk).
Bake 7 to 8 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all together and freeze.

title: mary jane's baked asparagus
directions: Put asparagus in large jelly roll pan.
Drizzle oil and sprinkle with salt, pepper, parmesan cheese, garlic powder and bread crumbs.
Turn until evenly coated.
Then arrange in a single layer.
Bake at 425°.
Roast for 10 to 15 minutes or until tender when pierced and tips start to brown.
Serve immediately or cool in pan.
Cover and refrigerate.
To reheat turn oven to 350° for 5 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Can be made up to one day ahead of time.

title: meat stew
directions: Cut meat into 1 1/2-inch cubes and roll in flour.
Put shortening in fryer cooker.
Set thermostat at 350°.
When sizzling hot, add meat in several portions.
Brown on all sides. Add salt, pepper, bay leaves and water.
Cover and simmer on low for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until
meat is tender.
Add more water if needed.
Add vegetables and simmer, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes more until they are tender.
With a slotted spoon, remove meat and vegetables onto a serving dish.
Discard bay leaves.
Thicken boiling gravy to desired consistency with flour and water paste, using 1 tablespoon flour to 2 tablespoons cold water for each cup of liquid.
Pour hot gravy over meat and vegetables.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: meatza pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Pat and fit into pie plate as pastry.
Spread catsup over top.
Sprinkle with sharp cheese, oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 or 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Yields 4 servings.

title: horton's hot chokes
directions: Drain and mash artichokes; blend with cheese and mayo.
Fill a small baking dish or quiche dish.
Bake 300° for 30 minutes. Serve with crackers (Triscuits are great).

title: baked brisket of beef...a winner!(and so easy)
directions: Place beef in covered roasting pan.
Pour Coke, dry onion soup mix and chili sauce over brisket.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 to 5 hours, until fork-tender.
Sauce is gravy.

title: country breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch dish.
Line bottom of dish with bread. Brown sausage and drain well.
Top bread with sausage, cover with cheese.
Mix eggs and milk.
Pour over the bread, sausage and cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend together to make base on bottom of baking dish.
Good idea to refrigerate base overnight.

title: holiday cake
directions: Make cake according to directions on cake mix.
Allow cake to cool thoroughly.
Poke each cake layer with fork in several places.
Mix each box of Jell-O separately with 1 cup boiling water and pour one kind of Jell-O over one layer and the other Jell-O over the other layer.
Allow to cool in refrigerator.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour out on floured surface. Roll out dough.
Cut and put in pan.
Grease top of biscuits before baking.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Boil sugar, water and cornstarch until thick, about 8 minutes. Remove from heat; add jello (dry) and a few drops of food coloring.
Fill baked pie shell with fresh strawberries.
Pour cooked mixture over strawberries.
Chill.
Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Yields 1 gallon of punch base.
Mix with 1 gallon of Sprite or ginger ale.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons sugar, crushed pretzels and oleo.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 8 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.
Mix the cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1 1/2 cups of sugar.
Beat well. Layer on top of pretzel mix.
Mix jello as directed.
When partly jelled, add fruit and nuts.
Pour over mix and refrigerate.
Slice and serve.
Good!!

title: wassail
directions: Place all the ingredients in a large pot.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: no bake coconut candy
directions: Beat softened cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar, blending thoroughly.
Beat in vanilla and salt; add just enough food coloring to tint.
Refrigerate, covered, for 1 hour.
Shape into teaspoon size balls.
Roll in coconut.
Place on cookie sheet, covered with wax paper, refrigerating for several hours or until firm.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute seasonings (onions, bell peppers, shallots and celery) in butter. Add soup and stir until creamy. Add 1 pound crawfish tails. Cook on medium to low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: steamed chinese sausage with potatoes
directions: Put sliced potatoes in a shallow dish. Add sliced Chinese sausages on top of potatoes.
Set dish on a rack in a pan.
Pour boiling water in the pan to within 1-inch of the rack.
Cover and bring to boiling and steam 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat 9-inch spring-form pan with nonstick cooking spray.
For crust:
In bowl combine graham cracker crumbs and 3/4 cup peanut butter.
Press onto bottom and 3/4 way up sides of pan; freeze 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Crust:
Place Melba toast in blender.
Make crumbs and put them in pie plate.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and diet sweetener.

title: french strawberry pie
directions: Spread softened cream cheese over bottom of pie shell.
Cover with 1/2 of strawberries, whole.
Take remaining strawberries and mash and strain until you have 1 1/2 cups of juice (if necessary, add water to make 1 1/2 cups).
Bring juice to boil and add mixture of sugar and cornstarch; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until boiling.
Boil 1 minute.
Cool.
Pour over berries in pie shell.
Chill about 2 hours before serving.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chocolate divinity candies(makes about 4 dozen candies)
directions: Combine sugar, salt, corn syrup and water in a 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves and mixture boils.
Continue cooking, without stirring, to 260° or until a small amount of syrup dropped into cold water separates into threads which feel hard but not brittle (soft-crack stage).
When sugar reaches 246°, beat egg whites in large mixer bowl until stiff peaks form.
When syrup reaches soft-crack stage, gradually pour in a thin stream into egg whites, beating at high speed on mixer.
Add vanilla and beat until candy begins to hold its shape.
Quickly blend in baking chocolate; stir in nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper-covered baking sheet.
(Divinity should be about the size of walnuts.)
Gently press a milk chocolate kiss on top of each piece.
Store in airtight container.

title: "tater" day sweet potato biscuits
directions: Wash sweet potatoes (taters).
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.
Let taters cool to touch, peel and mash.
Set aside 3 cups; keep warm.
Combine yeast and warm water in 2-cup liquid measure cup.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine flour and sugar in a large bowl.
Cut in Crisco a little at a time; blend until mixture is crumbly.
Add yeast mixture and warm sweet "taters"; stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out on lightly floured board.
Knead 5 minutes.
Place dough in a lightly greased bowl; turn over until the top is greased.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or even overnight.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with 2-inch round cutter.
Put on ungreased baking sheet; cover and let rise in a warm place 20 minutes or until double in size.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 minutes or until brown.
Makes 7 dozen.
Also unbaked biscuits may be frozen up to 1 month.
Let thaw 30 minutes and rise 20 minutes.

title: banana nugget cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Cut in shortening.
Add egg, banana, oats and chocolate chips.
Beat thoroughly until blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.
Remove immediately.

title: hurry-up crescent rolls
directions: Mix yeast and water.
Let set 5 minutes.
Combine biscuit mix and sugar.
Stir in yeast mixture.

title: white yeast bread
directions: Use the warm water to dissolve yeast. Pour hot milk over butter, sugar and salt in a large mixing bowl. Cool to lukewarm and add yeast and 3 cups flour; beat well. Add remaining flour and mix well. Turn out on floured board and knead well until smooth and satiny. Put in greased bowl; turn once and let rise until doubled in size, about 1 1/2 hours. Punch down and let rise 30 minutes. Makes 2 loaves or 12 biscuits. Bake at 400° for about 35 minutes.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let sit for 1 hour.
Bring next 5 ingredients to a boil; mix well.
Add squash and onion mixture; bring to a
boil and can.

title: corn meal waffles
directions: Stir together dry ingredients except corn meal. Stir in corn meal. Combine eggs, buttermilk and oil. Stir into dry ingredients. Mix only enough to moisten all flour. Bake in preheated (Pick-A-Pocket-Plus) or waffle iron. Makes 8 to 10 waffles.

title: baked custard
directions: Combine eggs and salt.
Slowly stir in slightly cooled milk, vanilla and sweetener.
Set six 6-ounce custard cups in shallow pan on oven rack.
Pour hot water 1 inch deep around them.
Pour custard in.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted off center comes out clean.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix and bake according to cake directions on box cake.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and add to jello when it has just begun to set.
Makes a large salad.

title: cream filled devil cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Add dry ingredients with milk and boiling water.
Drop by tablespoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: gingerbread waffles
directions: Bring molasses and oleo to a boil in a large kettle.
Remove from fire.
Beat in soda, sour milk and egg.
Add flour, ginger and salt.
Bake about 2 minutes on hot waffle iron.
Serve hot with whipped cream topped with cherry.
Makes 4 large waffles. Delicious.

title: pastry
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Sprinkle with water.
Mix with a fork.
Roll it out 1/8-inch thick.
Bake until done.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and milk. Heat to boiling. Boil 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Add butter, vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal. Drop on wax paper.

title: sweetheart punch
directions: Combine lemonade, orange juice, water and cranberry juice. Blend well.
Chill.
Pour in carbonated beverage just before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: scotch cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Mix in flour, baking powder, salt, oats, coconut and vanilla.
Drop on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: puppy chow snacks
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter in microwave.
Put powdered sugar in large, clean brown bag.
Add peanut butter to chocolate chips and butter.
Mix well.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal in brown bag.
Shake well.
Will keep in covered container a long time.

title: spinach salad
directions: Set jicama, spinach, mushrooms and green onions to one side for later.
Saute the remaining ingredients in 1/4 cup butter until brown.

title: ripe olive spread or dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Blend in sour cream; gently mix in bacon, olives, chives and horseradish. Makes 2 cups.

title: delectabites
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine butter, 1/4 cup powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix well. Gradually stir in flour, then walnuts.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake in upper third of oven at 350° for 10 minutes or until firm but not brown. Gently roll in powdered sugar. Cool on wire racks.

title: no bake fruitcake
directions: Crush crackers and mix with raisins, pecans and cherries.
Melt butter and marshmallows together.
Pour over other mixture.
Pack back in box or in a wax paper lined pan.
Put in refrigerator.
Can be frozen.
Dates and other candied fruit may also be added.
Pack tightly.

title: nut loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place pecans in the bottom of pie crust; bake until crust is golden brown.
Cool completely.
Beat cream cheese with sugar until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip and vanilla extract.
(You may substitute 3/4 cup heavy cream, whipped with 1 cup powdered sugar, then mix in 6 ounces cream cheese until smooth.)
Pour mixture over cooled crust and level.
Top cream layer with blueberry pie filling.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken with spicy fruit sauce(low-fat, low-sodium and sugar-free)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large, non-aluminum skillet; bring to a boil.
Add chicken; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until chicken is done.
Remove from skillet and keep warm.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Combine zucchini, pepper and onion.
Sprinkle with salt and celery seed. Let stand for 1 hour.

title: hamburger and spaghetti
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Break the spaghetti and cook and drain.
Mix all together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with a layer of American cheese and a layer of Parmesan cheese. Bake in a 350° oven about 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes; drain all water off potatoes.
Add sugar and butter; mash potatoes.
Mix sugar and butter.
Stir evaporated milk in.
Add spices.
Beat eggs and stir into pie mix.
Pour into pie crusts.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain.
Mix all ingredients except a small amount of cheese and cracker crumbs.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruity sherbet punch
directions: Combine juices in a punch bowl. Stir in ginger ale.
Top with sherbet. Serve immediately. Yields 15-20 servings.

title: lamb shish-kabob(souvlakia)
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate for at least six hours or preferably overnight.
(Pork or sirloin beef may be substituted.) Put meat on oiled wooden or metal skewers and set to grill over charcoal or gas grill, turning to brown evenly.
If regular oven is used, turn on broil; put skewers on rack and broil 6-inches from broiler, turning meat to brown.

title: southern cream cookie
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour cream; mix well.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.	Drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Grease bottom of a glass; dip into sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Press cookie flat.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.	Makes 6 dozen.

title: chocolate peanut butter crunch
directions: Melt chocolate chips and
mix
in
peanut butter (microwave). Add
cornflakes.	Mix
until well blended.
Drop
by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Place
in freezer until hard 10 to 20 minutes.
Remove and
store in refrigerator until serving time. Use a small melon baller to make uniform size balls.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix one cup of flour and one cup beer in a mixing bowl.
Cover and put in refrigerator for 8 hours.
Cut onions into rings.
Dip onion rings into batter.
Fry onion rings in Crisco until golden brown.
Approximate cooking time, four minutes.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Heat milk and cocoa in saucepan until warm.
Mix flour, eggs and sugar together.
Slowly add to milk and cocoa mixture.
Stir constantly until mixture is thick and creamy.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
In a pan or dish of your choice, layer bottom with vanilla wafers.
Cover wafers with pudding. Alternate until all pudding is gone.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate with shortening.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into greased baking pan (8 x 8-inch).
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
While warm, cut into strips or squares.
Remove from pan when cool.
These harden with standing.

title: 7 layer goodie
directions: Pour melted margarine into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer each ingredient as listed in pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Cool completely; slice into bars.

title: my favorite peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place by rounded teaspoonfuls on greased pan.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: hundred dollar chocolate cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, soda, baking powder and cocoa. Then add cold water.
When mixed thoroughly, mix in salad dressing.
Can bake as loaf or layer cake; use any chocolate icing for the top and sides.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Have butter at room temperature.
Combine butter, flour and sugar.
Add pecans and vanilla.
This will be a stiff dough.
Roll small amounts into small balls or finger shapes.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool completely. Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Mix together all ingredients; mix until dry ingredients are dampened.
Mixture will be lumpy in appearance; fill oiled muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dr. pepper punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and stir until sugar is dissolved. Add cooled club soda and Dr. Pepper just before serving.
Stir and enjoy.
Yields 1 punch bowl full.

title: pan gravy
directions: Place meat on warm platter; keep warm while preparing gravy. Pour drippings from pan into bowl, leaving brown particles in pan. Return 2 tablespoons drippings to pan (measure accurately as too little fat makes gravy lumpy).
Blend in flour (measure accurately so gravy is not greasy).
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in liquid. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir one minute. If desired, add a few drops bottled brown bouquet sauce.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first four ingredients together in a bowl.
Roll into balls and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax in a double boiler.
Put a toothpick in the ball and dip into the chocolate mixture.
Put each ball on wax paper to harden.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into two baked pie shells. Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.
The longer refrigerated the better it is.

title: frozen ham sandwiches
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and refrigerate until mixture is spreadable. Split party rolls vertically. Cover tops and bottoms with butter spread. Add ham and cheese slices. Can freeze rolls in original package. Bake at 350° (covered in foil) for 35 to 45 minutes (frozen) or 30 minutes (thawed). Slice and serve warm.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate for a few hours or longer.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add strawberries, pineapple and bananas. Mix well and let congeal. Soften cream cheese; add sugar and vanilla, then set aside. Whip the cream and slowly add to cheese mixture. Spread on congealed mixture and sprinkle with nuts.

title: blender spaghetti sauce
directions: *All measuring is done after you have processed through the blender.
Simmer the tomatoes, green pepper, oregano, onions and garlic 1 hour, then add tomato paste, black pepper, salad oil, sugar and salt.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours more.
Freeze.

title: quick german chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Beat at medium speed for about 4 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Add cornbread mix, stirring until just moistened.
Pour batter into 10-inch cast-iron skillet, coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Yields 10 wedges.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind apples and cranberries together. Add sugar. Set aside. Mix Jell-O with hot water. Cool slightly. Add celery, nuts and pineapple. Add Jell-O with cranberry mixture. Pour into 9 x 13 glass dish. Chill.

title: quick tuna supper
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Drain.
Add cheese package, margarine and milk according to package directions.
Add tuna (drained), cream of mushroom soup and drained peas or mixed veggies, whichever you prefer.
Serve with salad for complete meal.

title: marinated vegies
directions: Combine all vegetables, tossing lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours or overnight.

title: sour cream coleslaw
directions: In a bowl, combine the sour cream, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Fold in carrots, radish, green pepper and onion.
Pour over cabbage; mix lightly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix with mixer until creamy.
Great dip for fresh fruit.

title: frosting
directions: Mix powdered sugar and cocoa together.
To this, add softened margarine, milk and vanilla.
Spread on brownies.

title: marshmallow fudge topping
directions: Mix brown sugar, cocoa and milk in a sauce pan. Cook and boil 5 minutes. Stir in butter and vanilla. Fold in marshmallows. Marshmallows will partially melt.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well. Press firmly into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sugar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed.
Mix well.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients; slowly blend in half and half.
Cook until it thickens in a double boiler.
Add vanilla and margarine. After margarine melts and stirs in, pour immediately into previously baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Return to 325° oven for 10 minutes.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix ingredients all together and beat well.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool in pan and then put icing on.

title: my favorite mexican dish
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion in a large skillet; add liquid ingredients.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
In an ungreased large pan, add a layer of meat mixture, then a layer of tortillas, (cut in fourths), using all of tortillas; add a layer of grated cheese.
Repeat in layers as above; top with grated cheese.
Bake; serve with a green salad.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mrs. sorenson's peanut butter finger
directions: Cream butter, white sugar and brown sugar.
Blend in egg, 1/3 cup peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and oats.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into an iron skillet or long cake pan.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: venus demilo soup
directions: Fry hamburg and onion until brown.
Pour off excess fat. Place meat and onion in large soup pot.
Add water, soup mix, tomatoes and bouillon.
Bring to boil.
Add macaroni.
Boil until macaroni is tender, then add 1 can mixed vegetables.

title: barbecue sauce 1
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally. This makes a thick, delicious sauce.
Great on pork or chicken.

title: ruby red raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add raspberries and stir until berries are thawed and separated.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan; chill until set.
Carefully spread with sour cream; chill.
Dissolve cherry gelatin in remaining boiling water.
Add pineapple and cranberry sauce; mix well.
Allow to thicken slightly.
Carefully spoon over sour cream mixture; chill. Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves, if desired.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs and buttermilk; add oats and mix well.
Stir in molasses and oil.
Combine flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Stir into egg mixture.
If batter is too thick, thin with a little milk.
Pour about 3/4 cup batter onto greased preheated waffle maker.
Bake according to manufacturers directions.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients
and
mix
well.
Roll in balls and place on ungreased	cookie	sheet
and
flatten
with fork which has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Beat all the ingredients with mixer.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: fat-free blueberry muffins
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add egg white, yogurt and vanilla and beat.
Add berries and beat.
Fills 16 cupcake papers. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Melt butter and mix with dry ingredients.
Pour peaches and juice over top of all.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: taffy
directions: Cook in iron skillet without stirring until it rattles hard in cold water.
Turn into a large buttered platter and turn in edge as it cools.
When cool, pull.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake
at 350° until done.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight and reserve liquid.
Mix all ingredients and cover with liquid.
Bake in 300° oven for 6 hours.
Check liquid hourly.
Uncover last hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add sugar and refrigerate. When ready to congeal, add chopped celery, nuts, cranberries, carrots and orange (peel too) that have been put through a food chopper.
Pour in salad dish and refrigerate.

title: sweet sour pickle solution
directions: Heat and pour hot over dill pickles. Add spices and green coloring.

title: ham and broccoli (green bean) casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli and drain or drain can of green beans.
Spread vegetable on bottom of ungreased casserole. Layer ham and cheese next.
Beat remaining ingredients by hand. Slowly pour into casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain.
Melt butter in same pot.
Add macaroni slowly to melted butter.
Top with tomato sauces, sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix gently with a fork.
Cover and cook for approximately 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Mix again and remove from heat.
Let stand covered for 10 minutes.

title: baked pizza sandwich
directions: Stir together Bisquick, egg and milk.
Spread 1/2 of this in bottom of 9-inch square pan, sprayed with Pam.
Pour on 1 can tomato sauce.
Place on 4 slices of cheese.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese (room temperature) with milk until smooth.
Add instant pudding; beat until thick and smooth.
Spread over cake when cool.
Dribble crushed pineapple over that.
Cover pineapple with softened Cool Whip, then refrigerate overnight.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt cake pan.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut on bottom of pan.
Mix cake as directed and spread over nuts and coconut.
Cream together sugar, margarine and cream cheese.
Spoon over cake mix without touching the edges of the pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes up to 50 minutes until edges pull from sides of pan.
Cool completely before turning out onto serving plate.

title: broccoli, cheese and rice
directions: Mix everything together.
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: molly's breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put bread, sausage and cheese in bottom of pan. Add milk, salt and mustard to beaten eggs.
Pour egg mixture over bread mixture. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or bake 30 minutes, cool
and freeze, then reheat for 30 minutes.

title: chicketti
directions: Bone, skin, cook and cube chicken breasts.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Mix mushrooms, soup, sour cream, water chestnuts and spaghetti together.
Place in casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, then Parmesan cheese. Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Freezes well.
Makes 8 servings.

title: best pickles
directions: Mix
enough
salt
and
water to cover.
Wrap allspice, cloves and
cinnamon in cheesecloth and place in each gallon. Let set
4 days.
Drain and soak in alum water 1 day (1 tablespoon
alum
to 1 quart of water).
Drain, soak in 1/2 vinegar and 1/2 water 1 day and drain.
Mix syrup of 1 cup vinegar and 3
cups
sugar.
Bring to a boil and pour over pickles.
Bring to boil 4 mornings and pour in jars or big crock.

title: mildred's heavenly hash fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill until served.

title: wheat bread
directions: Scald milk.
While milk is cooling, add sugar, salt and shortening to milk.
Add yeast to 1/2 cup warm water (115°) let stand a few minutes, then add to milk mixture.
Add dry milk, wheat germ, molasses, 4 cups water and wheat flour; mix well.
Let this rise until double.
It will look bubbly and spongy, then add white flour.
Knead in well.
Let rise once then form into loaves and place in greased pans.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 loaves.

title: shipwreck casserole *
directions: Arrange onions on bottom of greased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Place potatoes on top; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Spread ground beef, crumbled, over potatoes.
Season with salt and m.s.g.
Add uncooked rice, celery and kidney beans.
Mix together tomato soup, bouillon and water, and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over casserole and bake, covered, at 350° about 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes and rice are cooked.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Stir yeast into warm water. Add oil, buttermilk, sugar, soda and flour. Mix well until smooth. Cover and refrigerate. Use as needed. Keeps 5 or 6 days. Bake biscuits at 350° until browned.

title: rick's clam chowder
directions: In large pot add minced onion, celery, salt, garlic, pepper and cooking oil.
Stir and cook until onion is tender.
Add potatoes and clam juice only, set clams aside.
Add clam base and water, bring to a boil then simmer until potatoes are soft and tender.

title: super chocolaty cake
directions: Cook the pudding and let it cool a little.
Mix the dry cake mixes with the pudding, then add the bag of chocolate chips.
Put into a big, deep, rectangular pan that is lightly greased (bigger than the usual 9 x 13-inch pan).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (or probably a little longer).
Let cool.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: aunt lana's lasagna
directions: Cook noodles, brown hamburger and drain.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Bring to slow boil and let simmer approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Layer 3 to 4 noodles, 1/3 sauce, 1/3 Mozzarella cheese and pat with Ricotta or cottage cheese.
Repeat 3 times and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Let cool 5 to 10 minutes.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Clean onions; cut into 1/4-inch slices and separate into rings.
Combine slightly beaten egg yolk and milk.
Add flour, salt and 1 tablespoon melted Crisco.
Mix until smooth.
Dip onion rings in batter.
Fry in 3/4 inch Crisco heated to 375° in an electric skillet.
Cook until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs and pumpkin.
Blend in sugar, spice or spices, flour and salt.
Mix well.
Add milk.
Mix well.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes one pie (8 servings).

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add other ingredients and allow to congeal.

title: zesty beef corn bread dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet, brown beef, onion and garlic.
Drain.
Stir in ketchup and salt.
Prepare corn muffin mix according to package directions.
Spread half of batter into a greased 8 x 8-inch square baking dish.
Spoon beef mixture over batter.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Spread remaining batter over cheese.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt together butter and cream cheese in microwave and stir. Drain corn and mix together with butter and cream cheese mixture. Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until corn is bubbling.

title: french meat pie
directions: In a skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Saute onion until tender.
Remove and set aside.
Brown beef and pork together; drain.
Combine onion, meat, potatoes and seasonings.
Fill pie shell with meat mixture.
Top with crust; seal and flute edges. Make slits in top crust.
Brush with egg or condensed milk, if desired.
Either makes a pretty pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: zucchini-corn chowder
directions: Cut corn from cobs.
Saute bacon until crisp; crumble and set aside.
Add zucchini, onions, green pepper and garlic; saute in bacon drippings.
Add corn, water and all seasonings.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer slowly for 10 minutes. Combine milk and eggs.
Add to pot and simmer until thickened.
Do not allow chowder to boil.
Sprinkle in bacon bits.
Serves 6.

title: evelyn's cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal and sugar together.
Add milk and beaten egg. Add melted butter and oil.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: aunt marta's carrot mold
directions: Make jello using the water and pineapple juice.
Chill slightly.
Add rest of the ingredients to the sour cream and add to jello.
Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over moderately low heat (225°).
Add onions and cook until soft.
Add salt, potatoes and water.
Cover, cook over moderately low heat (225°), stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes.
Stir in hot milk.
Combine egg yolk and cold milk.
Gradually add to hot soup, stirring constantly.
Garnish with parsley before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: turkey saute
directions: Cook turkey and garlic in margarine over low heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in vegetables.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are heated, stirring occasionally.
Add cheese; stir until cheese is melted.
Serve over rice.

title: chuck roast
directions: Wrap in heavy foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours or so.

title: glazed cinnamon bars
directions: Combine oleo, sugar, egg yolk and salt.
Beat until creamy. Stir in flour and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Spread thick batter into lightly greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Beat egg white until foamy. Stir in powdered sugar.
Brush sugar mixture over batter.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
