While hot, cut into 48 bars.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: pepperoni pasta
directions: Cook pasta.
Heat oil over medium heat, add onion, garlic, pepperoni and peppers and cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, oregano and salt; cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover during the last minute to thicken sauce.
Drain pasta and serve with sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and carrot.
Drain.
Add other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into long baking dish. Bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together and pour into 9 x 9-inch greased pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts. Bake for 55 minutes at 350°. Serve cold with whipped cream.

title: stella dora mock cream puffs
directions: Add Cool Whip to softened cream cheese. Add powdered sugar and well-drained pineapple. Mix well together. Cut top off cookies and fill the bottom; put top back on and refrigerate.

title: salsa dip
directions: Fry sausage crumbly.
Stir Velveeta and salsa in a saucepan over low heat until Velveeta is melted.
Stir in sausage.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 3 cups.
You can microwave.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, place in loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: super icing for decorating
directions: Mix shortening and extract.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add sugar, one cup at a time, beating well on medium speed.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl often.
Icing should appear dry.

title: brownie mix
directions: Mix together, cutting shortening, and store in airtight container.
To make brownies, combine 2 1/2 cup brownie mix with 2 eggs, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fig preserves
directions: Place figs in a large bowl; sprinkle with soda.
Add boiling (3 quarts) water and soak for 1 hour.
Drain figs, rinse in cold water.
Combine sugar and 1 quart water in large Dutch oven. Bring to a boil and cook 10 minutes.
Add figs and lemon to syrup. Cook until figs are clear and tender (about 1 hour), stirring occasionally.
Spoon figs into hot sterilized jars.
If necessary, keep cooking until thick.
Pour syrup over figs, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Run knife around edge of jars to remove air bubble. Cover at once with metal lids and screw bands tight.
Process in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Yields 4 or 5 pints.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix and pour in unbaked pie crust for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: trail snack bars
directions: Melt butter in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows, stirring until melted.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring until well coated.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool. Cut into bars.

title: pot roast
directions: Place roast on very large piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil. Spread mushroom soup on top of roast.
Sprinkle onion soup on top of soup.
Seal foil tightly, leaving a couple of inches of space between foil and roast on top.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours. Transfer to casserole dish for serving.

title: caramel corn
directions: Slightly beat first 5 ingredients; cook in microwave until thick, then add remaining ingredients.
Cool.
Pour into your baked pie crust.
Add meringue.
Bake.

title: pretzels
directions: Toppings:
coarse salt, table salt, poppy seed, sesame seed, celery seed or garlic salt.

title: cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, add water, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into tube pan, bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Follow directions on stuffing and prepare.
Press stuffing in bottom of 10 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chopped chicken meat. Mix soup, milk and egg together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple ring fritters
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add milk and egg.
Beat well.
Peel and core apples.
Slice into rings, about 1/4-inch thick.
Dip apple rings into batter and drop into skillet with about 1/2-inch melted shortening.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Drain.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon or a dot of currant jelly in center.
Makes about 12 to 16 fritters.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar together; add applesauce.
Sift and measure flour.
Mix flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add flour mixture and raisins to creamed mixture.
Pour in greased Bundt pan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip banana muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

In a mixing bowl, combine sugar and butter; beat until creamy. Add bananas, eggs and vanilla; mix well. Add dry ingredients and mix just until moist. Fold in chocolate chips. Spoon into greased muffin tins. Bake 18 to 25 minutes. Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan. Makes 1 dozen.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box; set aside. Mix pineapple and cherry pie filling; pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour cake mix over pineapple-cherry pie filling. Pour butter over cake mix. Top with pecans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: crawfish supreme
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add crawfish and saute 10 to 15 minutes.
Melt cream cheese; add whipping cream and seasoning to taste.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: spicy potato soup
directions: Brown ground meat in a skillet.
Drain.
Add potatoes, onion and tomato sauce.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender and the soup has thickened.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: "chicago style" pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch pie pan.
Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Stir in tomato paste, 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer while preparing crust.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add seedless grapes.
You may put a layer of strawberries in bottom of glass dish.
Then put mixture on top and chill or you may serve the mixture by itself.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add egg yolks and sugar, beating until sugar is dissolved or about 2 to 3 minutes.
Lower mixer speed and add flour and baking powder.
Add hot milk and vanilla last.
Bake at 350° in ungreased tube pan for 45 to 60 minutes (until tester comes out clean).
Invert pan to cool.

title: beef-macaroni-cheese
directions: Prepare dinner as directed.
Combine remaining ingredients. Mix lightly.
Press meat mixture on bottom of 8-inch square baking dish.
Top with dinner.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove cover.
Continue to bake 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: chicken and mushrooms supreme
directions: Boil chicken with carrots and onion for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth; let cool slightly and separate meat from bones into large pieces.
Strain broth and skim fat.
Slice cooked carrots diagonally.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter; blend in flour and cook 2 minutes.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups broth.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Blend in cream and cheese. Saute mushrooms (slice them if too big) in remaining butter. Drain artichokes and cut in halves.
Layer carrots, chicken, artichokes and mushrooms in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole. Pour sauce over top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: green punch
directions: Mix ingredients in gallon container.
Finish with water to make 1 gallon.

title: brown stew
directions: Cover bottom of 4-quart pot with oil; heat.
Add onion.
In a plastic bag, add flour, salt, pepper and beef.
Shake until all is coated and drop meat in hot oil.
Discard remaining flour.
Add garlic.
Cover and brown meat 10 minutes.
Scrape bottom of pot to loosen anything that could burn.
Add potatoes, carrots and enough water to cover.
Mix and add beef cube and sour cream.
heat high until it boils; reduce heat and cook until vegetables are tender. Keep scraping bottom of pot.
Add Gravy Master for color, if needed.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together the first 4 ingredients.
Microwave for 4 minutes on High.
Stir well.
(*If using dry roasted peanuts wait until now to add them.)
Microwave 4 more minutes on High.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Cook 1 minute more on High.
Add baking soda, quickly stir until light and foamy. Immediately pour onto lightly buttered baking sheet.
Spread thin. When cool, break into pieces.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat egg until foamy; add sour cream and mix well.
Stir together dry ingredients and egg mixture until just mixed.
Bake in greased muffin tin at 450° for 20 minutes. Yields 12 muffins.

title: christmas tea
directions: Mix ingredients in large saucepan or coffee maker.
Heat apple cider and ginger ale adding cinnamon sticks and red hots until they dissolve.
Stir before serving.
May heat again if necessary.

title: aunt mae's fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together. Add to margarine.
Spoon fruit over mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Will be brown.

title: cinnamon spiced tea
directions: Place tea in a teapot; pour water over tea.
Let steep for 5 minutes.
Pour into 4 cups.
To each serving, add a dash of cinnamon and about 2 tablespoons of the condensed milk.
Stir to blend.
Makes 4 servings.

title: burrito beef bake
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet; drain fat.
Stir in seasoning mix packet, broth and water.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms and set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, combine milk and cheese; cook over low heat until cheese is melted.
Remove tortillas from plastic bag; warm in microwave. Put about 1/2 cup meat mixture on each tortilla; fold over and fold in ends.
Place seam-side down in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Pour cheese sauce over all.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with taco sauce.

title: corn pudding
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Mix eggs, flour, sugar and milk.
Add corn.
Place butter pats on top.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over corn.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.

title: crock-pot taco dip
directions: Preheat crock-pot.
Cook on medium.
Cook sausage, hamburger and diced onion together in frying pan; drain grease.
Place into crock-pot.
Add mushroom soup.
Cut up tomatoes.
Cut or shred cheese into small pieces so it will melt easily.
Stir together. Let all mixtures blend well.
Leave in crock-pot to warm.
Great for parties or family gatherings.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add milk, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix well. Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in pie crust (or shell) and refrigerate 4 hours. Serve with whipped cream dollops and crushed peanuts.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients; add raisins and caraway seed.
Stir well and add buttermilk to make a soft dough.
Add slightly beaten eggs, saving 1/2 tablespoon to brush the loaf.
Dough will be sticky.
Turn dough on well floured surface and knead 10 strokes. Shape into 2 loaves.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes, until golden brown.
Brush with eggs.

title: german chocolate sundae cake
directions: Bake cake following instructions; cool.
Poke holes in top of cake with a wooden spoon handle.
Pour caramel over top. Refrigerate several hours.	Frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with crushed Heath bars over top.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: This is a layered salad.
Start with lettuce, then cauliflower, then bacon, then onion, then grated cheese.
Mix sugar and bacon fat and sprinkle on top.
Then spread mayo on top like icing. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Mix just before serving.

title: rotel
directions: Put peppers and onions in blender to chop.
Put in large pot on stove, then add vinegar, sugar and salt.
Bring to boil.
Then simmer for 30 minutes.

title: canned ham
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into each hole until mixture is at the top of the can. Drop a whole clove through each hole. Return ham to oven and cook 2 hours at 325°. Remove and pour juice into serving pitcher. Open ham, slice ham and serve with sauce.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll into ball. Put reserved nuts on waxed paper. Roll ball over nuts until covered.

title: pizza hot dish(microwave)
directions: Crumble ground beef into 2-quart glass casserole; add onion and garlic.
Microwave uncovered 5 to 6 minutes or until meat is set, stirring once.
Drain.
Stir remaining ingredients except cheeses into meat.
Microwave covered 15 to 17 minutes or until noodles are tender, stirring 2 to 3 times.
Sprinkle with cheeses. Microwave uncovered 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until cheeses are melted.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix flour, baking soda and salt in one bowl. Blend the butter, sugars, vanilla and eggs in another. Combine the two mixtures, then throw in chips and nuts. Bake tablespoon size lumps for 10 minutes. Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda.
Cream the shortening until fluffy. Add sugar, eggs and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Stir in mincemeat.
Gradually add flour mixture, mixing well.
Drop by teaspoons 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderately hot oven (400°) about 12 minutes.

title: vegetable stir-fry
directions: Coat a wok with oil. Drizzle oil around top of wok, coating sides. Heat at medium heat (350°) until hot. add carrots and stir-fry 2 minutes. Add peppers; stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or until crisp. Remove from heat. Add green onions, corn and peas. Combine soy sauce and remaining ingredients. Stir-fry cook 3 minutes or until thickened.

title: salmon cheese pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and roll out.
Put 2/3 dough in a pie pan.
Layer salmon and onions on top of dough.
Sprinkle over top, cheese.
Cover with rest of pie crust.
Bake at 350° until golden brown or 30 minutes.
Serve creamed peas over top of each serving.

title: apple dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in greased flat pan. Bake 30 minutes in moderate oven.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: acorn squash - baked
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut squash into halves, crosswise. Brush cut surface of each half with melted butter.
Sprinkle each with salt.
Arrange, with cut sides down, in baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Turn squash, with cut sides up, brush with combined butter and corn syrup and bake about 30 minutes.
(Can also sprinkle with little nutmeg or cinnamon.)
Makes 4 servings.

title: gramma's blueberry steamed pudding
directions: This looks like a lot of work, but it is delicious.

title: mandarin delight(a new twist on an old favorite; nonfat and yummy!)
directions: Sprinkle Knox gelatine over fruit juice and let soak for 5 minutes.
Add boiling water and stir until gelatine is dissolved. Add 7-Up and stir.
Add yogurt and NutraSweet Spoonful.
Fold in oranges.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan; refrigerate at least 4 hours. Cut into squares and serve.

title: skillet beef
directions: Cut up meat.
Add soy sauce and stir-fry until brown.
Add 2 cups cooked egg noodles to meat.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Top with sour cream.
If you need more liquid, add 1/2 cup water.

title: aunt helen's stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a shallow pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Cut off top of potatoes.
Scoop out and mash thoroughly.
Add hot milk, 2 tablespoons butter, salt pepper to taste.
Beat well.
Refill shells.
Return to shallow pan.
Shortly before serving time put in 450° oven to reheat for 8 to 10 minutes, unless potatoes are very cold.
In that case, 5 minutes longer.

title: taco delight
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Saute onion and pepper and add to ground beef.
Lay one can of rolls on cookie sheet.
Spread ground beef mixture over rolls, cover with taco sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover this with remaining can of rolls.
Bake at 350° until rolls are brown.

title: apple roll
directions: Thinly slice the apples and set aside.
In a small roaster, combine water and sugar.
Put roaster on stove burner and heat until sugar dissolves.
In a large bowl, mix together the flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and oil or shortening.
In cup, beat the egg and add enough milk to make 1 cup. Add to mixture in bowl. Place mixture on floured surface.
Press dough with hands evenly to about 1/2-inch thick.
Place apples on dough. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Roll dough up around apples. Cut into sections.
Place sections in roaster. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Serve warm with milk and sugar and salty ham slice or bacon on the side.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Beat butter until creamy; add sugar.
Stir in remaining ingredients and blend well.
Chill dough until firm enough to shape.
Form into small crescents and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Cool and roll into powdered sugar.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except paprika in ovenproof dish. Sprinkle paprika over top and bake in 375° oven
about 15 minutes.

title: sweet soup
directions: Cut desired amounts of beef, mutton or lamb flanks into 9 x 7-inch pieces.
On each place smaller pieces.
Season with salt and pepper and layer with chopped salted onions.
Roll jelly roll-like and sew each roll firmly with cord, leaving one end open.
Using edge of spoon (wooden) stuff with onions until roll is full.
Sew open end closing it.
Boil in salted water until done. Then remove from kettle and put in press for several hours.

title: onion shreds
directions: Cut onions into 1/8-inch slices and separate into rings.
Mix flour, salt and paprika in plastic bag.
Add about 2 cups of onions and shake to coat with flour.
Remove onions from bag and repeat with remaining onions.

title: banana pudding pie
directions: For Crust: Spray a 9-inch pie pan with Pam.
Melt margarine. Add flour and pecans and mix by hand. Press into bottom and sides of pie pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Combine broccoli, cauliflower, bacon, onion and cheese in a bowl. In a small bowl, mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar. Pour over vegetables; let stand 15 minutes.

title: speedy beef stroganoff
directions: In skillet or chafing dish, brown meat in hot oil; add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is crisp-tender.
Blend soup, sour cream, mushrooms, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meat; cook and heat slowly.
Cook and drain noodles.
Toss with butter and poppy seed.
Serve Stroganoff over hot noodles.
Serves 4.

title: coffee cake
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients slowly until liquid form.
Stir frequently.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together first.
Add other ingredients.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix together.
Make into roll.
Chill.
Slice very thin. Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake 10 minutes at 425°. Yields 3 dozen wafers.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Heat beans and drain.
Combine milk, soup, pepper and salt. Pour over beans.
Put in casserole dish, adding 1/2 can of onions. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with remaining onions and pimento and return to oven for 5 minutes more.

title: kennedy pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar.
Add one egg at the time, until you use 6 eggs.
Beat in flour, baking soda and salt.
Add vanilla and the last 2 eggs.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake in cold oven at 300° for 2 hours to 2 hours and 15 minutes.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with sifted flour the coconut milk, shredded coconut and vanilla.
Bake in two 9-inch pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Plain milk
may be used if coconut milk is not available.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with fresh fruit.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Shake all ingredients together well. Store in glass containers. Put 3 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread in biscuit pan; crumble into large bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients, except dressing, cheese, bacon and tomatoes. Stir in dressing until moist. Pour into serving bowl and top with cheese, bacon and tomatoes.

title: coconut cake with lemon filling
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: baked "fried" chicken
directions: Skin chicken breasts. Melt margarine; set aside. Crush crackers. Roll chicken breasts in melted margarine, then in cracker crumbs. Place the chicken breasts in a casserole dish and sprinkle with garlic salt, if desired. Bake at 350° to 375° for about an hour. If breasts are large, it may take a little longer than an hour.

title: broccoli pesto spaghetti
directions: Prepare pasta in boiling water, according to package directions.
In food processor, with knife blade attached, blend cooked broccoli, broth, Parmesan, olive oil, garlic and salt until smooth.
Stopping processor occasionally to scrape down side. Drain pasta.
Toss with broccoli pesto.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: mother's spritz cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Mix the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 9 minutes.
Bake until set NOT brown.
Put dough in press and press out cookies on ungreased cookie sheet. (decorate if desired).

title: spinach artichoke spread
directions: Thaw creamed spinach and then press the water out.
Drain artichokes very well.
Then mince them.
Combine the artichokes and spinach, mixing well.
Season with the Parmesan cheese and garlic, again mixing well.
Add the salt and pepper.
Adjust any of the seasonings.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: rocky mountain fudge
directions: In saucepan, combine chocolate pieces, condensed milk and margarine.
Heat over low flame until chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat.
In
large bowl, combine marshmallows and peanuts. Fold in chocolate mixture.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan whose sides and bottom have been lined with wax paper.
Chill 2 hours, until firm.
Remove from pan; peel off waxed paper.
Cut into squares.

title: danish rings
directions: Mix slightly, butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Do not cream as for cake.
Add yolks of 2 eggs, slightly beaten and flour.
Roll into long finger rolls and cut and make into circles.
Dip each one in beaten egg white and mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup ground nuts.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into a loaf.
Put in a loaf pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 60 to 90 minutes at 300°.

title: baked beans
directions: Wash beans.
Soak beans overnight or parboil.
Cook at 325° for 5 to 6 hours.
Serves 125 people.

title: sausage squares
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Mix with cream cheese.
Spread 1 can crescent rolls in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan to make crust.
Top with sausage mixture. Top sausage mixture with the other can of crescent rolls.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt oleo; add garlic salt, Tabasco, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir together.
Take other ingredients and mix in aluminum roasting pan.
Pour oleo mixture over ingredients in pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Store in sealed containers or jars.
Makes great Christmas gift.

title: praline pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients in heavy saucepan; cook to a soft ball. Beat by hand until good consistency.
Spread on cake.

title: squash enchiladas
directions: Microwave in glass bowl with Saran Wrap, covered, the zucchini, onion, garlic, chili peppers and water.
Cook 5 minutes in microwave.
Put mushroom soup in blender with microwave veggies.
Blend until smooth; this is the sauce.

title: jerry's spinach salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Save a few egg slices to garnish.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until nearly done. Cook and grate.
Mix soup, onions and sour cream.
Layer potatoes, liquid, salt and pepper and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, oil, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough until firm, at least 1 hour.

title: parmesan cheese dressing
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a small mixing bowl and beat for 2 to 3 minutes with a wire whisk, blending well.
Pour into a pint jar.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before using. Shake well before serving.

title: cottage pie
directions: Saute onions, garlic and beef 10 minutes.
Add carrots, tomato paste, herbs and stocks.
Salt and pepper.
Bring to boil and simmer about 20 minutes until carrots are tender.
Discard bay leaf.
Keep warm.

title: cream spinach
directions: Cook and drain the spinach.
Melt the cream cheese and mix with the spinach.
Sprinkle the herb stuffing and butter on top of spinach.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° in a glass pie dish.

title: holiday bars
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour, 2 teaspoons almond extract and melted margarine.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 11 x 15-inch pan. Sprinkle cranberries and then nuts over top.
Press into dough slightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes for about 15 minutes.
Butter casserole dish. Mix ingredients; bake, covered, at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: caramel frosted fresh apple cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat eggs, oil and sugar together.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together and add to egg mixture. In another bowl, stir vanilla, apples, nuts and coconut together, then add batter.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.
Let cool enough to handle pan and turn out on rack to cool completely.

title: grandma hall's hoppin john
directions: Cook beans in boiling salt water until tender.
Add brown sugar.
Fry bacon and onions until bacon is crisp; drain and crumble bacon and add with onions to beans.

title: farm house cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy. Add sour cream and vanilla.
Sift all dry ingredients together. Add to creamed mixture.
Roll on a lightly floured canvas or cloth.
Roll dough about 1/4-inch thick and cut out with large round cookie cutter.
Place on cookie sheet; sprinkle with sugar, nuts or raisins.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cookies should be large, soft and thick.
Don't place them too close together.
They should puff up big and need space.

title: bacon-spinach quiche
directions: Prick bottom and sides of pastry with fork.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes until lightly brown.
Combine cream cheese and milk in saucepan, stir over low heat until smooth.
Gradually add this to eggs; mix well.
Saute onions in margarine.
Add onions and remaining ingredients to cheese mixture.
Pour in shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: betsy's cornbread
directions: Pour 1 tablespoon of oil in a 12-inch skillet and put it in a 400° oven to heat while mixing the ingredients together.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix ingredients together, except nuts.
Add the nuts and chill.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Place peppers, cut side down, in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch microwave-safe baking dish.
Cover with plastic wrap and cook on 100% power (High) for 6 to 8 minutes or until nearly tender, rearranging peppers after 3 minutes; drain.
Break canned chicken into chunks.
Combine chicken, corn, Spanish rice, frozen onions and pepper sauce in a 1 1/2 quart microwave-safe casserole.
Stir until lightly mixed and cook, uncovered, on High about 6 minutes or until heated, stirring after 3 minutes.
Turn peppers cut side up and mound chicken mixture into shells.
Cook, covered, on High for 2 minutes or until heated and peppers are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover and let stand until cheese melts (about 2 minutes). Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet and sour bites
directions: Mix jelly and mustard together.
Heat just to boiling point. Add hot dogs; simmer until absorbed, about 10 minutes.

title: cucumber kim chee
directions: Peel and seed cucumbers.
Slice thinly and sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Rinse and drain.
Toast sesame seeds in a skillet over medium heat; watch closely as they burn quickly. Stir often.
Combine sesame oil, sesame seeds, garlic and cayenne.
Toss with cucumbers.

title: hash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium casserole or baking dish, put hash.
Chop onions fine and stir in with hash, then level off the top.
Mix sour cream, mustard, salt and pepper together in a bowl. Pile in center of hash and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: thimble cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add the sugar and vanilla, then the flour, mixing well after each addition.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Using a lightly floured thimble, indent each ball.
Fill the depressions with a dab of preserves, taking care not to overfill.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 12 to 15 minutes until very lightly browned.
Makes about 40 cookies.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookie and set aside 1/2 cup.
Mix crumbs with butter. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix and make as you do homemade ice cream.
Yield:
4 quarts.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup until it forms hard ball. Pour over beaten egg whites slowly.
Add vanilla. Beat until it will drop by spoonful on buttered table. Add nuts (crushed), if desired.

title: grilled swordfish with avocado sauce
directions: Avocado Sauce:
Place avocado, wine, lemon juice and cilantro in blender.
Blend and thin with water if necessary.

title: orange sour cream cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Beat margarine and sugar in another bowl until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks one at a time.
Stir in orange peel and walnuts.
Add 1/3 of the dry ingredients and 1/2 of the sour cream and beat. Add 1/2 the dry ingredients and remaining sour cream and beat well.
Add remaining dry ingredients.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake one hour.

title: lacy raisin oatmeal wafers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Sift together the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Rinse and drain raisins.
Mix raisins with oil and water, then mix in sugar, vanilla, oats and nuts.
Blend in the flour mixture.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until crisp around edges.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: easy cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix above and put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Melt margarine.
Stir in corn flakes.
Spread over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cool pink lemonade pie
directions: Blend all ingredients and pour into prepared graham cracker crust. Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: molasses cream cookies
directions: Cream sugar, oil and molasses; add egg and buttermilk and mix well. Add dry ingredients, sifted together. Add vinegar and soda mixture; mix well. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Press out with fork or finger dipped in flour. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Freezes well.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar; add water.
Cook until clear; set off and add Jell-O.
Cool.
Put berries in baked crust and pour cooled mixture over berries.
Cool in refrigerator several hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Bring chicken broth to a boil in soup pot.
Add salt; stir in mixture of cold water and cornstarch.
Stir a small amount of hot broth into egg.
Stir egg into hot broth.
Cook until clear and slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Garnish with scallion.

title: fruit salad 2
directions: Pour all in a bowl and mix.
Put in refrigerator.
Cover and let chill.
One can of fruit cocktail may be added for more.

title: date nut balls
directions: Mix and cook the first 5 ingredients until they come to a boil.
Add Rice
Krispies
and
pecans.
Mix
with the other ingredients.
When cool, roll in coconut.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, cherries, marshmallows, pineapple and nuts.
Whip the cream.
Add to fruit.
Pour into dish and let set in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Serve.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Cool.
Add to Dream Whip.
Layer graham crackers, Dream Whip and cherry pie filling.
Make another layer of Dream Whip mixture.
Top with graham crackers.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples on bottom of baking pan.
Put everything but cinnamon and butter in a bowl and fork together until it becomes crumbs.
Spread on top of apples, then pour 2 sticks of melted butter on top and sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: corn salad
directions: In covered dish, mix all ingredients well.
Tastes better after sitting in refrigerator for 3 hours.
Stir before serving. Keep leftovers refrigerated.

title: broccoli rice
directions: Cook 1 cup rice and set aside.
Saute onion, celery, pepper until tender; add mushrooms.
Add cheez whiz, soup, and broccoli. Add rice to mixture.
Bake in a casserole dish, covered about 40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in salad bowl.
Combine next 3 ingredients and pour over salad.
This dressing is good with fresh fruit or well drained canned fruit.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook fryer until well done.
Remove meat from bone when cool.

title: peanut or pecan clusters
directions: Melt together. Stir in peanuts or pecans and spoon on waxed paper.

title: hearty steak soup
directions: Brown round steak in a little oleo.
Melt butter or oleo in large pan.
Add flour and mix well.
Add the following; round steak, carrots, celery, onion, beef bouillon cubes, Accent, Kitchen Bouquet, frozen vegetables, tomatoes.
Cook over low heat for 6 to 8 hours.
The longer the better.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce into pieces.
Put in bottom of bowl.
Sprinkle onion over lettuce.
Layer water chestnuts over onion.
Sprinkle peas over water chestnuts.
Mix sugar with Miracle Whip spread over peas.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over Miracle Whip.
Sprinkle bacon bits over cheese.

title: coconut fruit dip
directions: In a blender or mixer, combine the first 4 ingredients.
Mix for 1 minute or until smooth.
Serve with fruit.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: weight watchers beef goulash
directions: Broil meat on rack 5 to 10 minutes on each side. Combine remaining ingredients except noodles in heavy skillet.
Simmer, covered, for 2 hours until meat is tender.
Stir in noodles. Makes 2 portions.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together and pour into a greased 10 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until a silver knife that's been inserted in the middle comes out clean. You need no crust for this one.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, vanilla, egg and milk until fluffy. Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll out 1/4-inch.
Cut out cookies.
Bake on cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs on high for 10 minutes. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk. Beat well. Add flavoring and coconut and mix well. Pour in greased Bundt pan and place in cold oven at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: basic baked potatoes and mock sour cream
directions: Put the ingredients together in a blender and whirl them until smooth.
Makes enough to store in refrigerator for a week.
(Also makes excellent salad dressing.)

title: pizzelles
directions: *Don't use more than one cup and don't use oil substitute.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix pineapple, water sugar and jello; bring to a boil for one minute.
Put in large bowl until it starts to jell.
Add cottage cheese, dream whip, nuts and cherries; fold into mixture.
Grease a 9 x 12 pan with mayonnaise, and pour in ingredients.
Let sit 24 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: gumdrop coconut cookies
directions: Cream Crisco; add sugars and beat well.
Mix and sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add sugar mixture alternately with egg.
Add coconut and gumdrops, then oats and vanilla.
Mix well. Shape in small balls and press with a fork.
Bake at 350° about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: miniature macaroon surprises
directions: You will need 48 miniature muffin cups.

title: hawaiian ham glaze
directions: Combine juices and sugar; cook until thickened.
Score the ham in usual manner; spread with a portion of the glaze.
Stud ham with pineapple slices, maraschino cherries and whole cloves. Store the remaining glaze in the large kit-kup and add the glaze to the baking ham in 2 or 3 applications.
Baking time as directed on ham.

title: fair ears
directions: Thaw dough according to package directions. Cut into 12 pieces. On a lightly floured surface, roll out each of the 12 pieces into an oval about 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick. Heat about 1/2-inch oil in a heavy skillet at medium-high heat. Cook bread pieces, 1 or 2 at a time, in hot oil for 45 to 60 seconds per side or until dough is brown. Remove hot ovals with tongs and drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar which has been mixed together. The finished ears may be kept warm in the oven while frying the rest.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips.
Spoon into 6 ungreased 1-cup baking dishes. Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips.
Bake, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed on package.
Blend while hot into cake mix.
Pour into 13 x 9 1/2 x 1/2-inch greased cake pan. Sprinkle chocolate bits and walnuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: theressa's chocolate ice cream
directions: You can use all low-fat ingredients if you care to. Mix all ingredients together and freeze.

title: "millie's" james house scones
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in currants and orange rind.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Add egg and milk.
Stir until dough clings together.
Knead gently 12 to 15 minutes on a lightly floured board.
Cut dough into fourths and form squares about 1/2 inch thick.
Cut each square diagonally twice to form 4 triangles. Place squares on a lightly greased baking sheet (or freeze for future baking).
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown. Yields 16 scones.

title: seasoned scallops
directions: Heat oil and butter in small baking dish.
Add lemon juice, crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add scallops.
Toss to coat with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cook less if using bay scallops.

title: chess pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, combine sugar and cornstarch with wire whisk; beat in eggs, one at a time, until well blended.
Stir in lemon juice, butter and lemon rind until well mixed.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Place filled pie on rimmed baking sheet.
Bake 50 minutes or until golden and a thin knife inserted into pie about 1 inch from edge comes out clean. Cool on wire rack.
Serve warm or refrigerate and serve cold.

title: broccoli with stuffing
directions: Cook broccoli. Combine eggs, onion, soup and mayonnaise. Place layer of broccoli in a 2-quart casserole. Add layer of cheese. Pour small amount of sauce. Repeat layers until all is used. Top with stuffing mix. Sprinkle margarine on top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Mix together and chill.
Shape into balls and roll in bread or cracker crumbs; fry.

title: french apple pie
directions: Fill unbaked pie shell with apples, sliced thin.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Put water over apples.
Then mix together flour, brown sugar and margarine; mix these ingredients together until crumbly.
Place on top of apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until apples are done.

title: green beans piquante
directions: In saucepan, combine green beans, onion, water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook, covered, for 25 minutes or until beans are just tender; drain.
In skillet, cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Reserve 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside. Return drippings to skillet; stir in vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Pour sauce over drained beans in saucepan; sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Toss lightly to mix.
Cover and return to heat for 2 to 3 minutes. Serve at once.

title: michael's baked ziti
directions: In a skillet, brown sausage and ground beef; set aside.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, place 3 to 4 tablespoons of sauce evenly over bottom.
Layer noodles, meat, cheeses and sauce in 3 even layers, topping with noodles and sauce.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until cheese is melted and heated through.

title: yogurt parsley sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Serve chilled over salad, cold ham, cold chicken or hot spaghetti with Parmesan sprinkled on top.

title: never fail fudge or icing
directions: Fudge: Melt margarine in a heavy saucepan.
Add sugar, cocoa and sweet milk.
Mix well.
Bring to a full boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Do not stir while cooking.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool, then beat adding nuts if desired.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a large covered saucepan, cook onions and garlic in butter over medium - low heat for 8 - 10 minutes or until tender and golden, stirring occasionally.
Add water, bouillon, and worcestershire sauce and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Ladle hot soup into six ovenproof bowls. Top each with a piece of French bread.
Cut each slice of cheese in half and place over the bread.
Broil until cheese melts. Serve immediately.
Yield 6 servings.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Beat the eggs until foamy.
In a separate bowl, combine butter and sugar. Beat until light and fluffy. Blend in beaten eggs and stir until thoroughly combined. Set aside.
Combine flour and baking powder. Sift together 3 times.
Gradually add flour mixture alternately with the milk to egg mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix until well combined. Stir in vanilla.
Lightly oil and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan.

Pour in cake batter. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until a tester inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from oven and let stand out for 5 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on wire rack. Spoon whipped cream, sweetened with sugar, into center of ring.
Garnish with strawberry slices and orange rind, if desired.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Add sugar and flour to sour cream; mix peaches into cream mixture. Pour into pie crust. Place pastry strips on top. Combine salt, sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over top of pie. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: portuguese potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets with onions and drain.
Place in a large casserole dish.
Sprinkle garlic and parsley on potatoes and onion mixture.
Next, add cubed Velveeta cheese and bread.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and dried beef
directions: Grease bottom of baking dish with butter.
Clean chicken good. Cover bottom of dish with dried beef.
Next, lay chicken breasts over dried beef.
Pour the uncooked soup over chicken.
You may need to spread it out.
Cover dish with foil.
Bake for 2 hours at 325°.

title: sighs or suspiros
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl and beat on high speed until mixture stands in stiff peaks.
Line cookie sheet with a paper bag cut to fit and without wrinkles.
Drop teaspoon at a time onto cookie sheet, swirling a peak to top it off.
Bake at 325° until lightly colored.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove carefully.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions. Pour half into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add sugar, margarine and nuts.
Wrap some mixture around one marshmallow and roll in corn flake crumbs. Continue with entire mixture.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: grilled reuben juniors
directions: Spread half of the bread slices lightly with mustard, then with the corned beef spread.
Add 2 thin slices of Swiss cheese and a dollop of sauerkraut.
Top with remaining bread slices and grill slowly in a buttered skillet.
Remove when cheese is soft and bread is golden.
Makes 18.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle rice into baking pan; pour onion soup over rice.
Add 1 cup water.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper; place over onion soup.
Spread cream of celery soup over chicken. Bake uncovered in preheated 325° to 350° oven for 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours.
Add water, as necessary, to keep moist.
Curry powder may be added, if desired.

title: lemon dill salmon and potatoes
directions: Sprinkle salmon pieces with 1/4 tsp. of the lemon pepper. Melt margarine in 12 inch nonstick skillet over medium high heat. Cook salmon in margarine 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until salmon flakes easily with fork. Remove salmon from skillet. Heat potatoes and water to boiling in same skillet; reduce heat to medium low. Cover and cook 5 to 8 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Stir in peas. Cook 3 minutes. Stir in lemon juice, dill weed, remaining 1/4 tsp. lemon pepper and the salmon. Cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until hot.

title: instant cucumber pickles
directions: Slice the cucumbers very thin; layer in ice for 30 minutes or longer with the onion, also sliced.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a greased 2-quart baking dish, layer a third of potatoes. Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle a third over potatoes. Top with third of onion.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour a third over onions.
Repeat layers twice.
Combine bread crumbs and butter. Sprinkle over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes more.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: betty's cheese potatoes
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and salt.
Stir until well blended. Add milk slowly, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Add cheese (cut in chunks) and continue to stir until melted.
Cook potatoes until tender (I slice 1/4-inch thick).
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole; top with cheese sauce and bake 30 minutes at 350°, or until browned.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, onion and water in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover with casserole lid and microwave at High for 9 to 10 minutes or until squash is tender, stirring after 4 minutes.
Mash squash mixture with a potato masher.
Add next 5 ingredients; stir well. Cover with casserole lid and microwave at Medium-high (70% power) for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Yield:
6 servings (about 113 calories per serving).

title: cranberry salad
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Add sugar and salad dressing and beat.
Add fruit and nuts and fold in Cool Whip. Freeze in rectangular or square pan.
Minutes before serving, remove from refrigerator.

title: jello punch
directions: To cherry jello, add 2 cups plus 4 tablespoons boiling water. Stir until dissolved.
Add 3 cups cold water and lemon juice; chill.
Add chilled ginger ale before serving.
Makes about 20 cups.

title: potato candy
directions: Mix first three ingredients well.
Roll out flat and spread with a thin layer of peanut butter.
Roll up and chill in refrigerator.
Slice into pieces.
Potatoes should be cooked as usual, but no salt added.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick and sausage thoroughly.
Add cheese.
Roll into 75 balls the size of a walnut.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes on a cookie sheet.
Serve warm.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and add to the corn.
Mix lightly.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Keep pan with drippings warm.
Mix remaining ingredients together thoroughly with whisk and pour into warm pan.
Cook until thick and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Let cool briefly (10 or so minutes).
Crumble bacon over lettuce; pour on dressing and serve. Yield:
Makes enough dressing to coat 1 large head of lettuce.

title: soft molasses drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Combine soda and molasses and add to creamed mixture.
Gradually stir in flour, then add raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets and bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until browned.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, milk and cocoa; bring to a boil, then boil for 1 minute.
Add oats, peanut butter, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let cool good.
Then put in an airtight container with lid.

title: plum pudding
directions: Make muslin cloth 1 yard square.
Combine Crisco, sugar, cinnamon, cloves, soda and eggs.
Beat well.
Add fruit and flour alternately.
Put in center of cloth.
Pull ends up and tie tightly.
Place in 5 quarts boiling water in 10-quart kettle. Boil 3 hours.
Remove pudding and sauce from kettle.
Save broth for sauce.

title: cheese and hamburger fondue
directions: Brown hamburger and drain fat.
In a small crock-pot melt the Velveeta cheese.
When cheese is melted, add meat, onion and Ro-Tel.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop corn; add nuts and salt.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Add brown sugar and water; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Boil without stirring to soft ball stage (238°).
Put popped corn and nuts in buttered roaster.
Pour caramel mixture over them and mix well.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve
Jell-O
in
the hot water.
Add the pineapple juice. Cool
until
it
starts to thicken; then add the cream cheese and blend with beater.
Add the whipped cream, pineapple and nuts. Chill until firm.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar and powdered sugar.
Add ice cream, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mix well and pour hot water over this for 1 cup of hot buttered rum.
Makes about 40 cups.
May freeze leftovers for later use.

title: cranberry orange muffins
directions: Cut cranberries in half and set aside. Beat together the egg, orange juice, oil and orange rind. Add the flour, baking powder and sugar. Stir until all ingredients are moistened. Add the cranberries and spoon into an oiled muffin tin or paper muffin cups.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream the sugars and shortening until smooth. Add egg.
Mix well.

Mix soda and 3 tablespoons water. Add to sugar mixture and mix well. Sift flour mixture. Blend well. Add remaining ingredients in order listed, mixing well after each addition. Pour mixture on wax paper.
Form into roll.
Chill thoroughly. Slice.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.
Yields 10 dozen cookies.

title: chili
directions: Cook and stir hamburger, onion and garlic in 3-quart saucepan until hamburger is brown, then drain.
Stir in tomatoes, chili powder, salt, sugar, Worcestershire, beans and red pepper sauce. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer.

title: oregon apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg.
Mix flour, soda, salt and spices together then add to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla, apples and nuts.
Bake in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Best when served warm with ice cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Boil chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
In a large mixing bowl, combine chicken, soup and chillies.
Mix well.
Crush tortilla chips in the bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish.
Spread chicken mixture over tortilla chips and sprinkle the top with lots of cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees until bubbly.
Serve with yellow rice.

title: barley pancakes with banana
directions: In a medium bowl sift together flour and baking powder.
Stir in the barley.
In a small bowl whisk together the milk, banana, egg and syrup.
Pour the mixture into flour.
Combine quickly (don't overmix). Heat nonstick frypan or well seasoned cast-iron skillet over medium-high heat.
Add 1/2 oil.
Spoon in 1/4 cup of batter for each pancake.
Cook until bubbles form on top of each, then flip.
Top with tasty low-fat all fruit, preserves or butter-fruit purees, unsweetened berries or nonfat yogurt.

title: spicy mexican bean soup
directions: In soup pot, cook bacon until crisp.
Discard half of bacon drippings.
Add onion, celery, green pepper and garlic, saute until tender.
Blend in chicken broth, refried beans, pepper and chili powder.
Bring to boil; remove from heat immediately. Garnish with chips and cheese.
Makes 8 cups.

title: garlic batter bread
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups of the flour, the yeast and salt in large mixer bowl.
In saucepan, heat milk, sugar and butter until warm (125°).
Butter does not need to be completely melted.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
When well mixed, fold in the Cool Whip; chill.

title: favorite banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix, milk and condensed milk in medium bowl.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In large bowl, layer pudding mix, wafers and bananas.
Continue to layer until pudding mix is used (about 3 to 4 layers of pudding).
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 8 to 24 hours for best results.

title: teen mix
directions: Cut bacon in strips and cook with the onion in a large kettle. Do not brown bacon until crisp.
Should be barely cooked.
Add ground beef and brown.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients and stir gently.
Cover kettle and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.

title: ham and cheese biscuits
directions: Spray medium skillet with cooking spray.
Add ham in hot skillet and saute 3 minutes.
Combine ham after cooked with flour and next 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Add milk, stirring just until moistened.
Drop batter by heaping tablespoons onto a baking sheet (spray cookie sheet).
Bake at 400° for 22 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: sausage swiss muffins
directions: In a small skillet cook sausage over medium heat until no longer pink. Drain. In bowl combine the egg and milk. Stir in dry ingredients just until moistened. Fold in cheese and add sausage. Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 375 degrees for 15 to 18 minutes. Cool for 5 minutes before removing from muffin pan. Serve warn. Refrigerate left overs.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix all together except chicken and a little cheese.
Pour half of mixture over meat and fill 8 flour tortillas.
After filling tortillas, lay in glass baking dish and pour remaining soup mixture over top.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
These may be frozen.

title: chili quiche appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch. Sprinkle chilies and cheese in pan.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender or 1 minute by hand.
Pour into pan.
Bake about 30 minutes until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Cut into 1 1/4-inch squares.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cocoons
directions: Mix together and shape into cocoons.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until they are tan.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: dump cake
directions: Place in layers in a 13 x 9-inch pan:
pie filling, pineapple, dry cake mix, shredded coconut and chopped walnuts.
Melt oleo or butter.
Spread across the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: texas jalapeno jelly
directions: Blend peppers and 1 cup white vinegar until pureed.
Pour into a large saucepan and add sugar, 1/2 cup white vinegar and cayenne pepper.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring frequently.
Stir in Certo.
Boil 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and skim off foam.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal. Yields 6 to 7 half-pint jars.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain the cherries and pineapple, reserving juice.
Heat the juice; dissolve the gelatin in it.
Cut the cream cheese into very small chunks and add to the gelatin mixture.
Add the cherries, pineapple, Coca-Cola and pecans.
Pour into a mold and chill.

title: spicy meat pie
directions: Saute meat, onion, and garlic in large skillet.
Stir in next 6 ingredients.
Mix cornstarch and water; stir in gradually.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Prepare pastry.

title: spanish cheese limas
directions: Cook beans in boiling water 15 to 20 minutes or until tender, drain.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Place the first 4 ingredients in bottom of the casserole. Melt stick of butter and add other three ingredients.
Put on top of casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients.
Pour other ingredients in and mix.
Knead lightly.
Roll out in circle 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in greased pan with edge of biscuits touching.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix flour, meal and sugar and sift together.
Add to eggs.
Add milk and lemon juice.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook brown and white sugars, butter, milk and salt to soft ball stage.
Add marshmallows and peanut butter just before removing from heat.
Add vanilla and beat until creamy and thick. Pour into a buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Store in a sealed Tupperware container.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream sugar with Crisco.
Separate eggs.
Add the egg yolks to sugar mixture.
To this, add vanilla.
Sift together the flour, salt and soda.
Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Add beaten egg whites.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pizza soup
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium heat.
Cook onion, bell peppers and garlic in oil, until onion is tender.
Stir in water, diced tomatoes and tomato paste until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients except bread and cheese.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Just before serving, heat oven to 425°.
Place bread on ungreased cookie sheet.
Toast bread in oven about 6 minutes, turning once, until brown.
Set oven control to broil.
Pour hot soup into 6 ovenproof soup bowls or casseroles.
Top each with 1 slice toast. Sprinkle with cheese.
Broil soup with tops 3 to 4 inches from heat for 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: aunt michelle's snickers salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill until ready to eat.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Boil
white
sugar,
2	sticks	butter	and cream for 7 minutes.
After
it starts to boil, take off and put marshmallow cream and chocolate chips in mixture.
Beat until glossy. Put in greased dish.

title: gary's oatmeal batter bread
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour and next four ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix water, milk and oil in a pan and heat until very warm. Add wheat germ to dry ingredients and pour heated liquid into it. Beat with mixer at medium speed; add egg and continue beating 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour, making a stiff dough.
Cover until doubled in size, about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir batter down before spooning into a greased loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes, until the loaf sounds hollow when tapped.
Remove from pan; brush top with butter and wrap in a clean dry towel for a few minutes.
Unwrap and continue to cool. Makes 1 loaf.

title: supreme apple bars
directions: Beat sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla with a mixer until light and fluffy. Combine flour, soda, cinnamon and salt. Fold into the egg mixture until blended. Add chopped nuts and apples. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13 pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey roll-ups
directions: Saute onion and celery in 1/3 cup butter until tender; add bread cubes, bouillon, parsley and seasonings; stirring well. Spoon about 1/3 cup stuffing in center of each piece of turkey; roll up lengthwise, tucking edges inside.
Secure each roll with a wooden pick.
Dredge turkey in flour; dip in 1/4 cup butter.
Place in a lightly greased 9-inch square baking dish; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 20 minutes or until done.
Garnish with lemon and lime slices.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream Crisco. Gradually add sugar.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt. Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix the two mixtures together.
Add milk and flavoring. Blend thoroughly. Mix raisins with 2 tablespoons of flour. Warm raisins and then add to mixture.
Add preserves and cherries. Then add nuts. Bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Then turn oven to 275° until done.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: Put milk, sugar, salt and butter in saucepan and heat until lukewarm.
Add yeast, which has been dissolved in water, to mixture in large bowl.
Cover and let rise 15 minutes.

title: grannie's peanut butter cookies(makes 32 bars.)
directions: Place butter in microsafe bowl, breaking it up into pieces. Microwave at High power for about 45 seconds.
Cover with wax paper to prevent spattering.
Beat in the sugars, vanilla, peanut butter and eggs.
Combine flour, bran, oats and baking soda.
Stir into butter mixture.
Press out half of dough into an 8 x 8-inch microsafe dish.
Shield corners of dish with foil to prevent overcooking.
Microwave at High power for 4 to 5 minutes, turning a quarter turn 3 times during baking.
Cool before cutting into bars.
Repeat with second batch of dough.

title: guacamole
directions: Chop the avocado, onion and eggs.
Thoroughly mix together with the cheese.
Stir in the lemon juice.
Use as a dip or side dish.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on tortillas.
Roll up and chill, then slice.
To soften tortillas for easy rolling, microwave for 10 seconds.

title: yum-yum
directions: Bake potatoes, cut lengthwise and remove contents so as not to break shells.
Mash, season with sugar and butter and add chopped nut meats.
Refill shells.
Cover with finely chopped nuts. Sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Reheat in oven for a few minutes.

title: fast, easy baked beans
directions: Drain about 1/2 the liquid off each can of beans.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in baking or casserole dish.
Top with 3 or 4 strips of bacon.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Add to macaroni, peppers, celery and carrots. Toss together until blended. Makes 5 cups.

title: corn pone
directions: Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Bake or boil chicken until tender.
When done, dice or tear chicken.
Boil potatoes, carrots and celery together until firm, but done, then add cans of vegetables.
While cooking vegetables, prepare pie crust.
In bowl, mix soup and milk and stir until smooth.
Layer in crust:
Soup, chicken, vegetables, salt and pepper.
Continue to layer until mounded.
Cover with crust.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° until crust is golden brown.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all of the ingredients into a bowl.
Mix on fast speed for about 10 minutes.
Pour into a container and refrigerate.

title: baked mostaccioli with sausage and peppers
directions: In a large skillet, stirring frequently, brown sausage with peppers and onion over medium-high heat 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Spread 1 cup of sauce in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with half of the Mostaccioli, 2 cups Mozzarella cheese and the Parmesan cheese.
Spread 2 more cups sauce.
Layer the remaining Mostaccioli cheese, sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons margarine until soft.
Make paste of flour and water.
Stir in onion.
Cook until thick.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine with mixture 1/2 of crumbs and Cheez Whiz; mix gently with beaten eggs.
Turn into greased casserole. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Stir in sugar, salt and oil.
Add 2 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead 5 minutes.
Place in lightly greased bowl and turn greased side up. Cover and let rise until double.
Dough is ready when indentations remain when touched.
No oil or cornmeal needed to spread this dough.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan or dish at 300° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk jello salad
directions: Bring pineapple (including juice) to boil.
Add Jell-O and mix thoroughly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in buttermilk.
Cool in refrigerator for 1 1/2 hours or until thick.
Blend in Cool Whip and extras, if added.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until firm.

title: english toffee
directions: Cook the sugar and butter in heavy boiler on medium heat. Will get foamy.
Stir constantly until golden and to a hard crack stage.
Pour over chopped pecans.
Lay 2 to 3 Hershey bars on top. After they melt (look dull), spread over top.
Let cool; break into pieces.

title: mustard honey bake chicken
directions: Stir together mustard and honey.
Dip chicken pieces in mustard mixture, then roll in crumbs.
Arrange on greased baking sheet. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: chocolate cookie
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar, then add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Shortening will float on top when mixer is stopped.
Add dry ingredients by hand.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until center springs back.
Rises like a cake.
Ice when cooled if you wish.
You may also add nuts.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Finely chop artichokes.
Add in the rest of the ingredients. Mix and bake for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate bubble biscuits
directions: In
large
bowl,
combine
flour, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Using pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in 1/3 cup butter
until
mixture
resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Add milk.
Stir until dough holds a shape. On floured
board,
knead
dough lightly.
Roll dough into 16 balls. Preheat oven to 375°.
In small saucepan, melt remaining 1/3
cup butter.
Pour
1/2 of melted butter in an 8-inch square
baking pan.
In
cup, combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar and
cinnamon.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix onions, taters and cheese.
Mix soup and sour cream. Combine both mixtures.
Put corn flakes on top.
Put butter on top of corn flakes.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour (when starts to brown).

title: pizza casserole
directions: Bring to boil and add 8 ounces medium noodles, uncooked.
Put in casserole dish and bake 20 minutes at 350°, then cover with cheese and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer, until cheese melts.

title: grilled fish
directions: Marinate fish for 30 minutes in mixed ingredients.
Cook on grill about 8 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Baste fish while grilling and sprinkle with paprika.
Baste shrimp or scallops only, don't marinate.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Bake pie crust at 400° for 3 minutes.
Remove and prick gently several times.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Dip zucchini in egg, milk and flour.
Fry until brown.
Make layers of zucchini, onion, tomatoes and cheese in casserole dish. End with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 more minutes.

title: virginia's spoon bread(the very best)
directions: Set oven
at
Heat
milk to scalding; add butter and salt.
Slowly stir in cornmeal.
Cook one minute, stirring constantly (use
eggbeater).
Remove
from heat and cool a few minutes, then
stir in well beaten egg yolks.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: mexican chip casserole
directions: In a skillet cook beef, onion, and garlic until meat is browned and onion is tender; drain.
Add soup, corn, and chilies; mix well.
In an ungreased shallow 3 qt. baking dish, layer meat mixture, corn chips, and enchilada sauce; top with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 8-10 minutes, or until heated through. Yield 6 servings.

title: copper polish
directions: Mix to a smooth paste.
Use like a regular polish for copper.

title: pinwheel candy
directions: Mix vanilla and cream cheese icing.
Add enough powdered sugar to make "dough".
Roll out flat.
Spread on peanut butter.
Roll up and chill.
Slice.

title: codfish a la vizcaina(bacalao a la vizcaina)
directions: Soak codfish in water to cover for 4 hours.
Drain well and boil rapidly in 2 quarts (8 cups) water for 15 minutes.
Drain, discard skin and bones and shred flesh.
Mix tomato sauce, water, olive oil, pimientos, olives, bay leaf, capers, raisins and garlic. In a large frying pan, arrange alternate layers of codfish, sliced potatoes, sliced onions and mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Cook over low heat covered for 30 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken until tender and chop or shred.
Saute onion in a small amount of oil.
Cook until clear.
Add the cream of chicken soup, the Ro-Tel or picante salsa and the cumin.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 cup sour cream.
Fry tortillas only until soft (2 to 3 seconds on each side).
Drain on paper towels.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Debone and cut into small pieces.
Set aside. Cook broccoli.
Mix together mayonnaise, broth and soups.
Mix in chicken and broccoli.
Put in casserole dish.
On top, add cheese and crumble Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° until brown for about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: *Add in desired amounts.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Form small balls and flatten with a fork.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; grease 2 loaf pans.
Combine sugar, pumpkin and eggs in a large bowl.
Beat until blended.
Add oil and beat.
Blend in flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in raisins.
Fill pans 3/4 full.
Bake about 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool.
Enjoy.
Can be frozen.
Makes two 1 pound loaves.

title: granny's mush
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add meal while boiling.
Mix well. Then add salt.
Cook until thick.
Mix 1 cup mush with small bowl of milk and serve.

title: tuna melt
directions: In mixing bowl, combine tuna, mayo, onion and celery; mix well. Top 4 of the bread slices with 1 cheese slice. Spread tuna mixture over cheese slices and top with remaining bread slices. Spread each sandwich with additional mayo. Place in skillet. Cook on medium heat until lightly browned on both sides. Makes 4 servings.

title: festive jello salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, celery, mayonnaise and nuts.
Let stand at room temperature.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add applesauce and cinnamon.
Pour half of mixture in pan and let congeal.
Spread a layer of creamed mixture over congealed layer. Top with remaining gelatin mixture.
Let congeal.
Cut into squares.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 8.

title: chicken baked with potatoes(pollo di patate al forno)
directions: Clean and cut up chicken.
Place chicken in baking dish (skin side up).
Place
onions
and
potatoes
around chicken. Dot with butter and
pour olive oil over chicken and potatoes. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake
at
for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, turning once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Separate rolls.
Combine chopped meat and cheese.
Reserve about half the mixture for use in the sauce.
Place about 3 tablespoons remaining meat/cheese mixture on each roll, then roll up.
Place roll seam side down in a slightly greased 7 1/2 x 11 3/4-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and milk together.
Add reserved meat and cheese mixture and pimento.
Pour over roll-ups.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix with electric mixer; let set 1 hour at room temperature.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish, layer pats of butter, apples, yams, brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Alternate until all ingredients are used.
Cover and bake 35 to 40 minutes or until apples are tender at 350°.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and brown.

title: white onion soup
directions: Cook sliced onions in broth 20 minutes.
Add potatoes and cook 15 minutes longer.
Puree in blender or use potato masher.
Melt butter in another pan.
Saute chopped onions until golden.
Blend in flour.
Add cream and milk.
Cook until thick.
Add to puree mixture.
Bring to boil and season.

title: ellie's chicken
directions: Put all ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Make sure chicken is coated well.
Bake at 350° until chicken is done, about 1 hour.

title: southwestern chili sauce
directions: Make a paste of chili powder and a little cold water; add to salted boiling water with the fat; stir to blend, then simmer to the consistency of tomato sauce for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add garlic. For thicker sauce, add more chili powder.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: cool carrots
directions: Cook carrots until crisp.
Mix and pour all other ingredients over hot carrots.
Refrigerate for 8 hours to marinate.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion.
Drain off grease.
Add bacon, catsup, salt, brown sugar, vinegar and dried mustard.
Add, in order, the pork and beans, kidney beans and lima beans.
Mix well and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook on medium heat about 10 minutes until slightly softened.
Add all other ingredients except cheese.
Cover and cook 35 minutes.
Top with cheese and serve with Italian bread.

title: oriental cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, Ramen noodles and sunflower kernels in bowl.
In a small bowl, add together sugar, rice vinegar, oil and seasoning packet from Ramen noodles.
Mix very well and add to slaw mixture. Best the first day.
Pretty good the second day.
Getting old the third day.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Mix and put in 9 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle over pumpkin mix, 1 yellow cake mix, 1 cup chopped nuts and 1 stick margarine (melted and drizzled over the top).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Cube a loaf of French bread.
Set aside.
Melt butter and cheese in a pan on low heat or in a fondue pot.
Add crab and garlic powder.
Dip bread in fondue.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Spread icing on warm cake.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix and cook at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: heidi's mother's lasagne
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add all other ingredients except cheeses and noodles.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Alternate layers in two 9 x 14-inch dishes: noodles (bottom), Jack cheese, cottage cheese and meat mixture.
Repeat process.
Sprinkle lots of Parmesan cheese on top.
Makes two 9 x 14-inch casseroles.

title: bean dip
directions: In blender, puree pork and beans and cottage cheese until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring over low heat, until cheese is melted.
Pour into chafing dish.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: da's chocolate pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add liquids; cook over medium heat, stirring until thickened.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/3 cup sugar; beat until creamy.
Pour on top of pie and place in a 350° oven until brown.

title: disaster cake
directions: In mixing bowl with electric mixer, combine ingredients and mix well.
Spread mixture on top of cake mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Place on rack to cool.
Cut cake in small squares and serve from pan.
Cake is very rich.

title: death by chocolate trifle
directions: Bake brownie mix according to package directions.
While baking, mix together chocolate syrup and the kahlua.
Pour about half of this mixture into trifle or serving dish.
When the brownie is done and cooled, break up and put into the dish on top of the syrup mixture.
Mashing it is okay.
Break up Heath or Skor bars and sprinkle some between layers.
Pour half of remaining syrup mixture on top of brownie mixture and refrigerate.
Make mousse according to package directions.
Spread mousse on top of cake.
Sprinkle with broken Heath or Skor bars.
Spread whipped topping on top.
When serving, serve with whipped topping and drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Beat together the shortening, sugar and vanilla at high speed until
mixture resembles ice cream.
Thoroughly beat in the eggs one
at a time.
In a pint measuring cup mix buttermilk
and soda.
By
hand
stir
the	flour
into the creamed mixture alternately
with
buttermilk
mixture,
only
until smooth.
Turn into
10-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325°
for
1 hour and 20 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Do not oven oven door.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray Bundt or tube pan with Pam. Combine white sugar with cinnamon in a bowl with a lid.
Melt butter in a small saucepan.
Add light brown sugar.
Stir until dissolved (should have a syrup-like appearance).
Add nuts.
Keep mixture warm, but do not boil it away.
While butter is melting, cut biscuits in quarters (this works better if you put cans in freezer 10 to 15 minutes before cutting).
Put them in the bowl of white sugar and cinnamon.
Put lid on and shake.
Layer biscuit quarters and then a layer of the brown sugar and butter mixture. Continue to layer both.
(Important:
Last layer must be butter with mixture.)
Cook no more than 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Remove bones from chicken and set aside.
Mix soups, Ro-Tel, pepper and onion.
Break tortillas in bite-size pieces.
In the bottom of an oblong, greased pan, put a layer of tortillas, then a layer of chicken, then a layer of mixture.
Continue the layers until all are used.
Cover with cheese and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop corn and place in paper bag.
In large microwave-proof mixing bowl, melt oleo.
Add brown sugar, Karo and salt.
Cook on High until starts to boil; stir occasionally.
Boil for an additional 2 minutes on High (do not stir during these 2 minutes). Remove bowl and add soda and vanilla.
Stir until evenly mixed and foamy.

title: elizabeth oat scones
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add wet ingredients.
Mix. Add raisins.
On floured wax paper, pat dough into 8-inch square. Using a pizza cutter or sharp knife, cut into triangles.
Brush scones with melted margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar. Transfer scones to ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 14 to 16 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water until tender.
Drain and break up, but do not mash.
Brown green onions in butter and stir into the celery soup.
Add eggs, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Combine the soup mixture with the squash.
