Put into a buttered casserole and cover with the grated cheese and additional bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Cook at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: yule cake
directions: Mix nuts and fruit together in large bowl. Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Sift over fruit mixture, mix well. Beat eggs until light, add vanilla, blend thoroughly into fruit mixture. Grease and line a 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan. I use waxed paper. Spread evenly in pan, Bake at 300 degrees for 1 1/2 hours until top in firm. Let cool 10 minutes, remove paper cool completely, wrap with rum cheese cloth.

title: congo squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening and add brown sugar.
Stir until well mixed.
Allow to cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and chocolate.
Pour in greased 11 x 16-inch pan.
Keep mixture approximately 3/4 inch in depth. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: carrots
directions: Cook carrots and drain.
Slice peppers and medium onion on top. Mix other ingredients and pour over carrots.
Serve cold.

title: creamy potato puff
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and potatoes, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in a 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: french toast
directions: For traditional sunny-side up eggs, melt 1 or 2 Tbsp. of butter in a 8- inch non-stick omelet pan or skillet over medium heat. Break open eggs into pan and immediately reduce heat to low.
Cook slowly until the whites are completely set and the yolks begin to thicken, but are not hard.
For ever easy flip over for 15 seconds. Serve immediately.

title: stella henson's pound cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, making two 8-inch layers.
When completely cooled, split both layers (I use a string put around middle of layers and pull together.
It cuts evenly, no mess.)

title: liz's cheese roll
directions: Let cheese come to room temperature.
Pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Shape into four rolls and roll in Gebhardt's chili powder.
Keep refrigerated.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter until soft, then put in casserole dish with other ingredients.
Put Cheez Whiz on top. Bake at 325° for one hour (uncover for the last 15 minutes).

title: easy ice cream
directions: Mix pudding and some milk well.
Add condensed milk.
Put in churn; add fruit.
Finish filling to the line with the milk. Churn until hard.

title: molasses bread
directions: Sift flour and salt together, set aside. Cream the margarine and sugar then beat in eggs. Stir in the molasses. Combine baking soda and buttermilk; add to creamed mixture and mix well. Combine with flour. Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar until creamy. Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Add cake mix and apricot nectar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each one.
Bake in tube pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 325° or until done.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; blend with mixture. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt
margarine in an 8-inch baking dish in oven.
Make a batter of sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over margarine, then add fruit and juice.
Bake at 350° until dough is brown and cooked through fruit, for 50 to 60 minutes. For larger cobbler, double and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Start in cold oven.
Mix together the oil, sugar, eggs, apples and nuts.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt into mixture.
Add vanilla.
Start in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 80 minutes or until middle comes out clear.

title: painted cookies
directions: Mix.
Wrap in wax paper and chill 4 hours.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put white sugar, Karo and water in a saucepan.
Stir only to dissolve sugar.
Cook until 295° or hard tack stage.
Leave on the fire.
Add peanuts and oleo; stir.
Remove from heat; quickly add soda and vanilla.
Pour on a greased cookie sheet.

title: weight watcher's chocolate-mint parfaits
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium saucepan; stir well. Cook over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Remove sauce from heat and stir in mint flavoring.
Spoon 1/4 cup ice milk into each of 4 parfait glasses. Top each with 1 tablespoon chocolate sauce.
Repeat procedure with remaining ice milk and chocolate sauce.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon chopped pecans over each serving.
Garnish with fresh mint sprigs, if desired.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings with about 156 calories per serving.

title: dump-it-cake
directions: Spread ingredients in order.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and oil.
Mix together and let marinate overnight.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese, cracker crumbs and butter.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with cheese, then cracker crumbs.
Melt butter and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut bacon wraps
directions: Spread cracker on both sides with peanut butter.
Wrap a strip of bacon around each cracker.
Micro-cook on paper towel in roasting pan 4 minutes on High or until bacon is crisp.

title: corn and ham soup
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients, except cream.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, 15 minutes.
Stir in heavy cream.
Heat through.
Do not boil.

title: candy bar cushions
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Stir in flour.
Place "half" of dough in cookie press.
Using ribbon plate, press strips on ungreased cookie sheets.
Break candy bars into squares.
Place candy pieces 1/2 inch apart atop dough strips.
Lightly press candy into dough.
Force remaining dough through press in strips over candy.
Mark between candy with knife.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 13 minutes.
Immediately cut into cookies where marked.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: tom's deep fat fried chicken
directions: With mixer, beat eggs, flour, salt, pepper and milk until smooth.
Dip each piece of chicken in batter and roll in bread crumbs.
Lightly brown in deep fat.
Arrange in shallow pan and bake in a 325° oven for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: the clogging doctor's cajun hush puppies
directions: Mix well and let sit 30 minutes.
Cook 2 to 4 minutes at 400°. Remove from cooking oil and place on several thicknesses of paper towels, removing oil.
Enjoy!

title: working woman's lasagna
directions: Start noodles boiling.
Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and cottage cheese to hamburger and simmer. Drain noodles.
Lay flat on wax paper to avoid sticking.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan completely with Pam.
Cover bottom of pan with noodles.
Spread hamburger meat mixture on top of noodles and sprinkle with cheeses.
Continue layering noodles, meat and cheese until all ingredients are used.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: apple custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: jello ice cream
directions: Dissolve one package Jell-O in cup of hot water.
Beat together 2 level cups of sugar and 3 eggs.
Add Jell-O and beat. Add enough milk to make required 3 quarts.
Flavor to taste with vanilla and freeze.
Will make 3 quarts.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple, including juice, in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix, just as it comes from the box, over fruit.
Slice butter over dry cake mix.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pecan tassies
directions: To make crust:
Blend cream and stick of softened margarine. Add flour; chill about 2 hours or overnight.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Sprinkle dry onion soup on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: microbaked apples
directions: Fill apples with brown sugar; dot with butter.
Put apples in microwave dish.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes or until tender.

title: russian beet salad
directions: Drain beets.
Reserve liquid and slice into shoestrings.
Add enough water to beet juice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Bring to a boil. Add Jell-O and stir until Jell-O is dissolved.
Cool and add sugar, vinegar, horseradish and lemon juice.
Add beets and pour into a 9 x 9-inch glass dish; refrigerate until completely set.
Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add enough milk until it's like icing. Spread over top of salad and refrigerate until serving time.
Great for a buffet.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and garlic in oil.
Put tomatoes through blender or cut with edge of spoon.
Add tomatoes and remaining ingredients to beef, onion and garlic.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream butter. Gradually add sugar. Cream well. Add egg yolks and beat well. Blend together dry ingredients. Add to egg yolk mixture alternately with milk. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites, nuts and lemon peel.
Turn into 3 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: barbecued beef ribs
directions: Preheat the oven to 450°.
Place the ribs on a rack in shallow baking pan and roast for 30 minutes.

title: easy pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into a 17 x 10 x 1 inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° until done.

title: tea cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla, lemon extract and butter; sift flour and add to mixture.
Mix well to form a firm dough (some flour differs in texture, so you may need to add additional sifted flour to form firm dough).
Roll dough in waxed paper and refrigerate until firm.
Cut dough into round slices and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Mix the lemon Jell-O, orange Jell-O, sugar and crushed pineapple with juice.
Boil for 3 minutes.	Time when it starts to boil.
Add cold water.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch dish and chill until partially set.
Fold together Cheddar cheese, nuts and Cool Whip. Then fold this mix into Jell-O mixture.
Refrigerate until used. Serve on a leaf of lettuce and top with 1/2 teaspoon mayo dressing if desired.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: mrs. moss' class' classy dessert
directions: Line the cups of a standard muffin pan with cupcake papers. Place one vanilla wafer in the bottom of each cup.
Add, in this order, 2 banana slices, 2 tablespoons pudding and 1 tablespoon Cool Whip.
Top with sprinkles.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: angel biscuits no. 1
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Dissolve
yeast
in
lukewarm water. Sift
flour,
sugar,
salt
and soda together.
Cut in shortening.
Add
buttermilk and dissolved yeast.
Knead well, using more flour if dough is too sticky.
Dough may be covered and kept
in
refrigerator
for a week or may be rolled out at once, cut into biscuits and baked.
No need to let rise before baking. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: open face cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix cheese and dry dressing mix.
Spread on bread slices.
Top with a cucumber slice and garnish with dill weed.

title: hearty hamburg soup
directions: Melt butter in pan; add beef and brown.
Add onion and cook until transparent.
Stir carrots, potatoes, peppers, celery, tomato juice, seasoned salt and pepper together.
Cover and cook over low heat until vegetables are tender.
Combine flour and 1 cup of milk; stir into mixture.
Let boil.
Add rest of milk and heat, stirring.
Do not boil.

title: campbell's soup plus
directions: Prepare soup as directed on label.
Heat slowly.
Add canned tomatoes, basil and mushrooms.
Heat thoroughly and serve.

title: salsa mold
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in tomato and lemon juices. Stir in salsa.
Pour into a 5-cup mold.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.
Unmold.
Serve with tortilla chips, if desired.

title: linda's corn bread
directions: Mix well (by hand).
Grease pan and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: happy home recipe
directions: By Helen Steiner Rice.

title: magic brownie pudding
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Grease an 8 by 8 inch baking dish.Combine the flour, sugar, pecans, 4 TBSP cocoa, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl and mix well.
Stir in milk and oil. Spread in prepared baking dish.
Combine brown sugar and remaining cocoa in a small bowl and mix well.
Sprinkle the brown sugar mixture evenly on top of batter in baking dish.
Pour boiling water on top of brown sugar mixture.
Bake until set, about 35 minutes. Serve with ice cream, whipped cream or milk.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine first eight ingredients.
Form into 40 bite size balls, using a full teaspoon for each.
Brown lightly in oil. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Drain off fat.

title: aunt ettie's filled sugar cookies
directions: Chill dough before rolling.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.

title: mexicali dip
directions: In saucepan combine soup, cheese and salsa.
Over medium heat, heat through, stirring often.
Serve with tortilla chips for dipping.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: wonderful and easy chicken breasts
directions: Wrap chicken in bacon.
Use a toothpick to secure.
Cut beef in 1/2 inch pieces.
Put on bottom of quiche dish.
Place chicken on beef.
Blend sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with lemon pepper and parsley.
Bake for 3 hours at 275 degrees.
Do not cook at higher temperature.

title: tomato bouillon
directions: Bring to a boil in crock-pot.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve hot (freezes well).

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 9-inches.

title: buttermilk frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Boil mixture until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Pour over hot cake.

title: strawberries a l'orange
directions: Hull strawberries and cut into halves; arrange in serving bowl. Halve grapes and remove the seeds; add to the strawberries.
Cut, peel and remove the pith from 2 of the oranges; slice and add to strawberries in the bowl.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Trim excess fat off of roast.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in crock-pot with onion and green pepper.
Add 1/2 cup water. Cover and cook on high heat about 5 hours.
When roast is cooked, shred it with a fork and add barbecue sauce.
Serve on buns.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix milk, eggs, bread and vanilla. let set to soften bread. Mix with rice, margarine and sugar. Put in Pyrex dish at 350° until thick or brown (about 30 to 45 minutes).

title: chocolate banana bread
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender or two knives until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add bananas and eggs.
Blend well.
Pour into 2 (9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: eggnog
directions: Mix beaten eggs with sugar and salt in the top of a double boiler.
Add milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, just until mixture coats spoon, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool. Add vanilla.
Chill.
Immediately before serving, strain eggnog. Beat with rotary beater until frothy.
Pour into chilled cups. Sprinkle each serving with nutmeg as desired.

title: microwave corn
directions: Cut
off top or silk end of corn.
Do not shuck.
Place ears of	corn
in
microwave.
Do
not
cover
or wrap.	Cook approximately
minutes
per
each ear on High.
Take out of microwave when tender; season with salt, pepper and margarine. Shuck corn (silks will come off with shucks).
Eat and enjoy!!

title: apple pan douty
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift and add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Then add apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: linguine with spicy peanut shrimp sauce
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions.
While pasta is cooking, combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan and place over low heat.
Cover and simmer until the sauce is smooth and the shrimp are cooked through, about 2 minutes.
When pasta is done, drain well and transfer to a large bowl.
Add sauce and toss gently until well combined.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: 7-pound christmas fudge
directions: In a large mixing bowl of heavy-duty electric mixer, combine broken chocolate bars, chocolate bits and marshmallow cream; set aside.
In large heavy saucepan combine sugar, milk and butter. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils; boil 5 minutes.
Pour hot mixture over chocolate mixture.
Beat until ingredients are thoroughly blended.
Beat in vanilla, remove beater and stir in chopped nuts. Quickly pour mixture into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.
Cover tightly and refrigerate until firm enough to cut into small squares.
Flavor will be best after 1 or 2 weeks storage.
Makes about 7 pounds fudge.

title: pork tenderloin with mustard sauce
directions: Combine garlic and olive oil.
Rub on pork tenderloin and refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.
Grill about 20 minutes, turning often until done through.
Mix yogurt, mustard, sugar substitute and chives.
Serve sauce with grilled tenderloin.

title: pasta and ceci(chickpeas)
directions: In a saucepan in the oil, brown the onion and celery. Cook until tender.
Add the tomato puree and water.
Simmer about 1 hour.
Add the chickpeas and cook for 1/2 hour more.
Boil the noodles, drain and add to chickpea sauce.
Top with the cheese.

title: hot sandwich spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Is better if left to stand 30 to 45 minutes.
Spread on any kind of bread of your choice.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Combine shortening, butter and sugar.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and flavoring.
Stir in pineapple.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.

title: oven spareribs
directions: Brown ribs in frying pan.
Place in baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: working girl pie
directions: Melt butter or margarine in an 8 or 9-inch pie dish while oven is preheating to 350°. Set aside. Combine flour, sugar and about 1/2 of the milk. Stir until dry ingredients are moistened. Add remaining milk and stir until smooth. Pour batter over melted margarine. Do not mix. Place drained fruit over top of this mixture. Do not stir. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned and center springs back when touched with finger.

title: golden brown pork chops
directions: Prepare and
wash
chops.
Pat
dry.
Sprinkle spices on both sides.
The mayonnaise on both sides.
Coat and cover with flour. Heat oil, medium hot.
Add chops, fry on one side until brown, turn once.

title: $500.00 fudge
directions: Cook sugar and Pet milk to a rolling boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly. Use a large stainless steel pan; remove from heat. Add butter, chocolate chips, vanilla and salt. Stir until mixed. Pour into buttered pan; let stand for 6 hours before cutting. Will keep a long time in cookie tin or a sealed container.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, bananas, marmalade and water together. Sift
dry
ingredients and add to fruit mixture.
Stir in nuts. Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Time of preparation: 20 minutes.
Serves 2 loaves.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello with boiling water.
Add pie filling and pineapple with juice.
Let congeal.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream; add sugar.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Mix.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top of salad.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; add egg. Mix well until crumbly.
Melt butter in pan and stir in cinnamon. Peel and slice apples in a square baking dish.
Top with dry ingredients and pour butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: banana spice layer cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Add flour mixture alternately with bananas.
Beat well after each addition.
Turn into 2 well-greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 375° approximately 25 minutes.
(Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes.) Serve with Banana Butter Frosting (recipe follows).

title: barbecued short ribs
directions: In 8-quart Dutch oven, cover beef short ribs with water; over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 2 hours or until ribs are fork-tender.
About 1 hour before serving, in small bowl combine catsup and remaining ingredients. Pour sauce over ribs and either heat in oven until heated through or cook on outdoor grill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: kathy's pecan tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Form into small balls about the size of an English walnut. Place in small tart pans and press around bottom and sides. Sprinkle small amount of pecans in bottom and fill 3/4 full with filling. Sprinkle more pecans on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Put 1 to 2 tablespoons of mix in a cup of hot water.

title: date nut rolls
directions: Melt butter in pan or boiler over low heat.
Add beaten egg, dates and sugar.
Stir and cook.
Let boil about 6 minutes, until thick.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Add vanilla, nuts and Rice Krispies.
Mix thoroughly and shape into bite-sized balls, then roll in coconut.

title: swiss steak deluxe
directions: Cut steak into pieces; pound flour into sides and brown in hot oil.
Put in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over; cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover last 15 minutes.

title: tuna muffins
directions: Beat eggs and add to tuna, olives, lemon, seasoned salt, pepper and parsley.
Add rice and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix together; roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Roll into powdered sugar.

title: spicy chicken thighs
directions: Mix all the liquid ingredients and the spices. Pour mixture over chicken pieces to marinate for several hours. You can marinate the chicken pieces either
in a shallow covered pan, turning them every few hours OR put the chicken and the seasoning mixture into a tightly sealed plastic bag.

title: golden crisp brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix slightly crushed cereal, nuts, brown sugar, butter and 2 tablespoons of flour.
Pat into ungreased square baking pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Heat chocolate and Crisco in 2-quart saucepan over low heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Spread over layer in pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Loosen edges from pan.
Invert on wire rack.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars (about 2 x 1 1/2-inch).
Yields 24 bars.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Spray 9-inch pan with Pam.
Mix all ingredients, except strawberries and Cool Whip, together.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Shut oven off!
Keep door shut and leave in 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Top with fresh strawberries and Cool Whip!

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Thinly slice potatoes to cover the bottom of a greased baking dish or cake pan about 3/4 inch deep.
Season with salt and pepper. Mix diced meat (ham, sausage or bacon) into potatoes.
Thinly slice eggs and cover potato/meat mixture.
Make a medium white sauce and add enough cheese to make sauce a light yellow. 1 1/2 cups white sauce with 3 slices cheese covers an 8 by 8 inch pan.
Sprinkle paprika over top.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes in oven until heated through.

title: quick chocolate drops
directions: Blend melted chocolate with condensed milk and mix well.
Stir in nut meats or coconut.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield: 4 dozen cookies.

title: eva's creamy beef bake
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed on box.
Brown meat and onion in margarine.
Stir in soup and milk.
In a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer half of dinner and meat mixture. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken with soup and sour cream.
Spread in casserole dish.
In a separate bowl, mix butter and crackers.
Spread cracker/butter mixture over top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach pies
directions: Prick pie shells all over and bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
In large skillet melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Thaw spinach; drain and squeeze out by hand.
Add spinach to onions and cook and toss until all moisture has evaporated.
Remove from heat.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl, then add spinach to cheese and mix until it looks like marble; turn half into each pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until top is golden and filling is set. Remove from oven and serve warm or cool.
(To lighten, use light Ricotta cheese and no butter.)

title: stuffed squash
directions: Parboil whole squash, split and remove pulp, leaving a thick shell.
Chop pulp and onion; saute together in a little margarine or butter.
Mix in stuffing mix and fill squash shells.
Put shredded cheese on top.
Bake in at 350° oven until hot and bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat, salt and pepper and add chopped onions. Add tomatoes, beans, soup and rice.
Stir well and heat for about 10 minutes.
Serve over your favorite chips (Doritos, etc.).

title: oven barbecue chicken(super healthy version)
directions: Place together in blender the vinegar, oil, water, paprika, salt, pepper and onion.
Blend together until onion is quite finely chopped.
Add parsley and give just a whir to mix.

title: ham cakes
directions: Combine the ham and the bread.
Saute the onion and celery in 1 tablespoon margarine until wilted.
Mix sauteed vegetables with the ham and bread crumb mixture.

title: tangy fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding, Tang and undrained pineapple until dry ingredients are dissolved.
Add drained fruit cocktail and any fresh fruit you desire.
Chill.

title: upside-down taco
directions: Saute ground beef with onion; drain.
In a lightly greased container (10-inch pie pan or 9-inch square), layer the following: refried beans with sausage, meat mixture, taco sauce, chilies, Cheddar cheese, Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with sour cream before serving.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: kentucky jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light; add eggs.
Beat well after each egg is added.
Add jam and beat well.
Add sifted flour, soda, salt, cloves and allspice, alternately with buttermilk, beating until smooth.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 325° for about 35 minutes.
Frost with caramel frosting.

title: pineapple pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix above together; pour in 2 unbaked shells.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then turn oven to 350° for 20 minutes.

title: north carolina grilled turkey steaks
directions: Combine soy sauce, oil, sugar, ginger, ground mustard and garlic.
Mix well.
Pour over steaks, turning to coat both sides. Marinate in refrigerator 2 hours or up to 24 hours. Turn steaks in marinade several times.
Grill drained turkey steaks over medium hot coals, 8 to 10 minutes, per side, basting with marinade a couple of times, if desired.
Turkey steaks are done when there is no pink in center of meat.
Serves 4.
Marinade yields 3/4 cup.

title: round steak supreme
directions: Cut steak in 1-inch squares.
Coat with flour.
Beat eggs and milk in pie plate.
In another plate, combine crumbs, cheese and seasonings.
Dip meat into egg mixture and coat with the crumbs, cheese and seasoning mixture.
Brown meat in hot oil.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish.
Arrange slices of tomatoes on top of meat. Stir water into tomato juice drippings in skillet; heat to boiling, scraping brown bits from pan and pour over meat.
Salt and pepper.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Cook vermicelli according to package until tender.
Add lemon juice, salt and Accent.
Add the following to vermicelli mixture: bell pepper, pimientos, celery, olives, onions and mayonnaise. Chill.
I also like this without the mayonnaise.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: In frying pan, put the butter and lightly brown the onion, garlic and celery, only until soft, then remove from flame.
Then brown separately the ground beef and remove the grease.
Mix all ingredients and put in baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, covered.
Add Chinese noodles on top, uncovered.
Bake for 15 more minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: raspberry cloud souffle
directions: Select a few whole raspberries for garnish; freeze in small container until needed.
Soften gelatin in 3/4 cup cold water.
In heavy saucepan, combine raspberries, 3 tablespoons sugar, lemon juice and softened gelatin.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until gelatin is dissolved.
Cool.
Add kirschwasser.
Chill until partly set.
Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form; gradually beat in remaining 6 tablespoons sugar, continuing to beat until stiff, but not dry.
Fold egg whites and about 3/4 of whipped cream into partly thickened raspberry mixture.
Turn into prepared 1 1/2-quart souffle dish.
(See following.)
Chill until set, several hours or overnight.
Garnish with remaining whipped cream, reserved raspberries and green citron slivers for Christmas color.

title: bunch broccoli
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Cream together ingredients.
Bake in a greased cake pan. Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in large bowl.
Mix water and yeast, then add to first mixture.
Cover and place in icebox for 2 hours or overnight.
Take out and knead on floured board.
Grease pizza pan with shortening, then with hands.
Spread dough in pan, then put pizza sauce and toppings on top.
Bake at 450°.

title: golden pound cake
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream
sugar and shortening;
add eggs.
Sift flour and baking powder
and
add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Add peanut
butter and vanilla.
Bake in two layers at 350° about 25 minutes.
Test with a toothpick.

title: caramels
directions: Melt butter over medium heat; add brown sugar and stir until all lumps are dissolved.
Add Karo syrup and condensed milk.
Stir constantly until mixture reaches 236° to 238° or just short of soft ball stage.
Add vanilla and stir until mixture stops bubbling.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet.
Cool completely and cut into squares.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate or freeze.

title: crunchy chestnut meatballs
directions: Combine crumbs, milk, soy sauce, garlic salt and onion powder. Add ground beef, pork sausage and water chestnuts; mix well. Form meat mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a graham cracker crust. Put in freezer until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Brown onion in margarine.
Add 1/2 cup water and Cheez Whiz. Bring to boil and add thawed broccoli.
Put in casserole dish and bake 20 minutes.
Then cover with cracker crumbs and continue baking until brown.
This can be made the night before except for cracker crumbs.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In a bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat first 6 ingredients until fluffy.
At low speed beat in next 4 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and add taco seasoning.
Put mixture in the bottom of 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix together the refried beans and tomato sauce.
Pour over browned hamburger.
Top with grated cheese and crushed tortilla chips.
Bake in a 300° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve with tossed salad.

title: creamy avocado sauce
directions: Combine avocado, sour cream, lemon juice, onion, salt and chili powder. Chill. Stir in bacon, crumbled. Garnish with bacon curl.

title: chop suey
directions: Season steak and chop into bite size pieces.
Brown steak in oil in Dutch oven.
Add chopped celery, onion and 1/4 cup of water and saute; cover.
Mix flour and water together until flour is no longer lumpy.
Add 3 tablespoons of soy sauce to flour and water; mix well.
Pour mixture into steak and vegetables and stir until well blended.
Add more soy sauce for taste (add a little at a time).
For thicker gravy, add cornstarch.
Add water to thin gravy.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Stir in tomato paste, onions and seasonings (mixture wil be thick).
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Place biscuits in a greased muffin tin, pressing to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of meat mixture into biscuits-lined cups and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 12 pizza cups.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bring berries and 1 cup water to a boil and cook for 2 minutes. Strain, save the juice only.
Add sugar and Clear Jel.
Mix sugar and Clear Jell and moisten with a small amount of water before adding to juice.
Bring to a boil; set aside to cool.
When cool, add sliced strawberries; set aside.

title: chicken in a pot
directions: Truss chicken.
Melt butter in large skillet and brown chicken slowly (about 30 minutes).
Transfer chicken to a large pot.
Pour wine, broth and salt into skillet and bring to a boil.
Stir to get all brown bits.
Pour this over chicken.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 45 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Add vegetables in layers:
first potatoes, second carrots, third celery, then onions and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with rosemary and celery leaves.
Place chicken on top of vegetables, cover and cook for 45 minutes more. Cut up the chicken and arrange with vegetables on platter.
Fill gravy boat with remaining juices.

title: good everyday meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape in a loaf pan, rounding the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve warm.

title: chocolate truffle cake
directions: Melt butter and 16 ounces of chocolate in double boiler.
Add flour, 1/2 tablespoon sugar and water.
Whip with a wire whisk. Add egg yolks, one at a time, whipping constantly.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar until stiff but not dry.
Fold whites into chocolate.
Turn into 8-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
No longer!
Cool.
Whip cream with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Frost cake and decorate with chocolate curls.

title: poor man's beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, salt and pepper; drain.
Mix in next 3 ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Boil and drain noodles. Before serving, mix sour cream into ground beef mixture.
Serve over noodles and/or mashed potatoes.
